name: Abusive Sergeant
text: Battlecry: Give a minion +2 Attack this turn.
flavorText: ADD ME TO YOUR DECK, MAGGOT!

name: Ace Hunter Kreen
text: Your other characters are Immune while attacking.
flavorText: This grandmaster marksman loves winning tournaments and eating a bit of ice cream.

name: Acidic Swamp Ooze
text: Battlecry: Destroy your opponent's weapon.
flavorText: Oozes love Flamenco. Don't ask.

name: Acrobatics
text: Draw 2 cards. If you play both this turn, draw 2 more.
flavorText: He soars through the air with the greatest of fleas.

name: Adorable Infestation
text: Give a minion +1/+1. Summon a 1/1 Cub. Add a Cub to your hand.
flavorText: Some cards are strong by sheer power; others draw strength from love.

name: Aegwynn, the Guardian
text: Spell Damage +2 Deathrattle: The next minion you draw inherits these powers.
flavorText: With Medivh as her son, nothing YOU do could ever disappoint her.

name: Against All Odds
text: Destroy ALL odd-Attack minions.
flavorText: Time to EVEN out the playing field.

name: Aimed Shot
text: Deal 3 damage. Your next Hero Power deals 2 more damage.
flavorText: Wait, you WEREN'T aiming before?!

name: Akama
text: Stealth Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Akama Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: "To many of my people, I am known as a traitor... as Illidan's lapdog. I will remain in the shadows, for now... Actually, maybe I'll just remain in the shadows forever."

name: Al'Akir the Windlord
text: Charge, Divine Shield, Taunt, Windfury
flavorText: He is the weakest of the four Elemental Lords. And the other three don't let him forget it.

name: Al'ar
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 0/3 Ashes of Al'ar that resurrects this minion on your next turn.
flavorText: Week 679: Still no mount...

name: Aldor Attendant
text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of your Librams by (1) this game.
flavorText: Will check to make sure you have a valid libramary card.

name: Aldor Peacekeeper
text: Battlecry: Change an enemy minion's Attack to 1.
flavorText: The Aldor hate two things: the Scryers and smooth jazz.

name: Aldor Truthseeker
text: Taunt. Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of your Librams by (2) this game.
flavorText: It’s under 'T.'

name: Aldrachi Warblades
text: Lifesteal
flavorText: The ancient Aldrachi were the greatest warriors in the universe. Imagine their power if they'd put the handle at the END of the blade.

name: Alexstrasza the Life-Binder
text: Battlecry: Choose a character. If it's friendly, restore 8 Health. If it's an enemy, deal 8 damage.
flavorText: Friendly Fire: Off

name: Alliance Bannerman
text: Battlecry: Draw a minion. Give minions in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: Back in my day, we had to carry our inspiration uphill both ways to war.

name: Altar of Fire
text: Destroy the top 3 cards of each deck.
flavorText: "I now pronounce you, Crispy and Fried."

name: Ambush
text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, summon a 2/3 Ambusher with Poisonous.
flavorText: Clip-clop clip-clop CLIP-CLOP STAB!

name: Amulet of Undying
text: Tradeable Resurrect friendly Deathrattle (minion, minions). (Upgrades when Traded!)
flavorText: Didn't seem to work out too well for this guy.

name: Ancient Void Hound
text: At the end of your turn, steal 1 Attack and Health from all enemy minions.
flavorText: What happened to my 1/1 Void Pup? And the glee club?!

name: Ancient of War
text: Choose One - +5 Attack; or +5 Health and Taunt.
flavorText: Young Night Elves love to play "Who can get the Ancient of War to Uproot?" You lose if you get crushed to death.

name: Anetheron
text: Costs (1) if your hand is full.
flavorText: Leads every demonic invasion. Hopefully this one turns out better than the World Tree.

name: Animated Broomstick
text: Rush Battlecry: Give your other minions Rush.
flavorText: "Blimey, that's a Stratocumulus 1000!"

name: Annoy-o-Tron
text: Taunt Divine Shield
flavorText: The inventor of the Annoy-o-Tron was immediately expelled from Tinkerschool, Tinkertown, and was eventually exiled from the Eastern Kingdoms altogether.

name: Apexis Blast
text: Deal 5 damage. If your deck has no minions, summon a random 5-Cost minion.
flavorText: Lonely mages can still have a blast!

name: Apexis Smuggler
text: After you play a Secret, Discover a spell.
flavorText: "S-secrets? I don't have any! Whoa, look, a spell!"

name: Apothecary Helbrim
text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Add a random Poison to your hand.
flavorText: The best way to maintain your health is to poison everyone else.

name: Apothecary's Caravan
text: At the start of your turn, summon a 1-Cost minion from your deck.
flavorText: If you won't bring out your dead, we'll bring the dead to you.

name: Apotheosis
text: Give a minion +1/+2 and Lifesteal.
flavorText: Defined as the absolute pinnacle of existence. Plus Lifesteal.

name: Arbor Up
text: Summon two 2/2 Treants. Give your minions +2/+1.
flavorText: If you can’t outrun a tree, you really shouldn’t be here anyway.

name: Arcane Anomaly
text: After you cast a spell, give this minion +1 Health.
flavorText: He used to get work as a Spatial Anomaly, but he got tired of having his polarity reversed.

name: Arcane Devourer
text: Whenever you cast a spell, gain +2/+2.
flavorText: Likes her magic with a pinch of salt.

name: Arcane Intellect
text: Draw 2 cards.
flavorText: Playing this card makes you SMARTER. And let's face it: we could all stand to be a little smarter.

name: Arcane Luminary
text: Cards that didn't start in your deck cost (2) less, but not less than (1).
flavorText: They say true value is the cards you find along the way.

name: Arcane Overflow
text: Deal 8 damage to an enemy minion. Summon a Remnant with stats equal to the excess damage.
flavorText: On this ship, when you can’t use an int, learn how to float.

name: Arcane Shot
text: Deal 2 damage.
flavorText: Magi conjured arcane arrows to sell to hunters, until hunters learned just enough magic to do it themselves. The resulting loss of jobs sent Stormwind into a minor recession.

name: Arcanologist
text: Battlecry: Draw a Secret.
flavorText: What did you draw? Shhhh… it’s a secret.

name: Archdruid Naralex
text: Dormant for 2 turns. While Dormant, add a Dream card to your hand at the end of your turn.
flavorText: "Dormant? I think you mean naptime."

name: Archspore Msshi'fn
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Msshi'fn Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: Brave leader of the Sporeggar. Guided by the philosophy that one should not mssh with matters that are not one's msshiness.

name: Archwitch Willow
text: Battlecry: Summon a random Demon from your hand and deck.
flavorText: One of the demons will do all the work while the other gets the same grade.

name: Argent Braggart
text: Battlecry: Gain Attack and Health to match the highest in the battlefield.
flavorText: Not sure why he's bragging, he's got the same stats as the next guy.

name: Argent Protector
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion Divine Shield.
flavorText: "I'm not saying you can dodge fireballs. I'm saying with this shield, you won't have to."

name: Argent Squire
text: Divine Shield
flavorText: "I solemnly swear to uphold the Light, purge the world of darkness, and to eat only burritos." - The Argent Dawn Oath

name: Arid Stormer
text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, gain Rush and Windfury.
flavorText: Some people chase storms, some storms chase elementals.

name: Armor Vendor
text: Battlecry: Give 4 Armor to each hero.
flavorText: "You look like the kind of person that would buy three sets of armor. One to wear, a spare, and a spare for the spare."

name: Armorsmith
text: Whenever a friendly minion takes damage, gain 1 Armor.
flavorText: She accepts guild funds for repairs!

name: Ashtongue Battlelord
text: Taunt Lifesteal
flavorText: Demons have destroyed the lives of the Ashtongue draenei. Now he’s got a shoulder-axe to grind.

name: Ashtongue Battlelord
text: Taunt Lifesteal
flavorText: Demons have destroyed the lives of the Ashtongue draenei. Now he’s got a shoulder-axe to grind.

name: Ashtongue Slayer
text: Battlecry: Give a Stealthed minion +3 Attack and Immune this turn.
flavorText: Her other hand attachments include a corkscrew and a bottle opener.

name: Assassin's Blade
flavorText: Guaranteed to have been owned by a real assassin. Certificate of authenticity included.

name: Assassinate
text: Destroy an enemy minion.
flavorText: If you don't want to be assassinated, move to the Barrens and change your name. Good luck!

name: Astromancer Solarian
text: Spell Damage +1 Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Solarian Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: Loyal to Kael'thas Sunstrider, this blood elf mage sought arcane power in the Void. Did she find it... or did IT find her?

name: Athletic Studies
text: Discover a Rush minion. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: It's a quick read.

name: Auctioneer Jaxon
text: Whenever you Trade, Discover a card from your deck to draw instead.
flavorText: "Who's up for a brand-new wisp? This thing's in perfect condition, folks! Never been played..."

name: Auctionhouse Gavel
text: After your hero attacks, reduce the Cost of a Battlecry minion in your hand by (1).
flavorText: "I want to be a judge! Or an auctioneer! Look, all I want is one of those sweet, tiny hammers."

name: Augmented Porcupine
text: Deathrattle: Deal this minion's Attack damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Pokey-man. Gotta spike 'em all!

name: Auspicious Spirits
text: Summon a random 4-Cost minion. Corrupt: Summon a 7-Cost minion instead.
flavorText: "I'm not AWE-spicious, but I am a little spicious."

name: Avenge
text: Secret: When one of your minions dies, give a random friendly minion +3/+2.
flavorText: Several paladins have joined together to deliver justice under the name "Justice Force". Their lawyer talked them out of calling themselves the Justice League.

name: Babbling Book
text: Battlecry: Add a random Mage spell to your hand.
flavorText: His idol is the Green Hills of Stranglethorn, and he won't shut up about it.

name: Backfire
text: Draw 3 cards. Deal 3 damage to your hero.
flavorText: "That's the last time I let an imp spit gasoline into my car."

name: Backstab
text: Deal 2 damage to an undamaged minion.
flavorText: It's funny how often yelling "Look over there!" gets your opponent to turn around.

name: Balloon Merchant
text: Battlecry: Give your Silver Hand Recruits +1 Attack and Divine Shield.
flavorText: It's a shiny yellow balloon! But it can be popped with a single point of damage.

name: Bamboozle
text: Secret: When one of your minions is attacked, transform it into a random one that costs (3) more.
flavorText: "WE DO YOU A BAMBOOZLE, HOOMAN!"

name: Banana Vendor
text: Battlecry: Add 2 Bananas to each player's hand.
flavorText: There's always money in the banana stand.

name: Barak Kodobane
text: Battlecry: Draw a 1, 2, and 3-Cost spell.
flavorText: They say he's a pro at horseback archery.

name: Baron Geddon
text: At the end of your turn, deal 2 damage to ALL other characters.
flavorText: Baron Geddon was Ragnaros's foremost lieutenant, until he got FIRED.

name: Baron Rivendare
text: Your minions trigger their Deathrattles twice.
flavorText: There used to be five Horsemen but one of them left because a job opened up in the deadmines and the benefits were better.

name: Barrens Blacksmith
text: Frenzy: Give your other minions +2/+2.
flavorText: "Maybe someday you’ll make it to Gadgetzan, kid."

name: Barrens Scavenger
text: Taunt Costs (1) while your deck has 10 or fewer cards.
flavorText: When the hundredth centaur dropped, so did her bracers.

name: Barrens Stablehand
text: Battlecry: Summon a random Beast.
flavorText: It’s never Huffer.

name: Barrens Trapper
text: Your Deathrattle cards cost (1) less.
flavorText: Just add a bit of murloc meat for bait. Beasts can’t resist that special seasoning…

name: Barricade
text: Summon a 2/4 Guard with Taunt. If it's your only minion, summon another.
flavorText: The Alliance and Horde join forces to enforce the fire safety capacity.

name: Battlefiend
text: After your hero attacks, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: Say what you like about my hatchet-headed hooligan, he’s my battle-friend.

name: Battleground Battlemaster
text: Adjacent minions have Windfury.
flavorText: Farm! No wait… Mine! No wait… 3 to Smith—they're taking Farm. Get there now!

name: Bearshark
text: Can't be targeted by spells or Hero Powers.
flavorText: "Candygram."

name: Beastmaster Leoroxx
text: Battlecry: Summon 3 Beasts from your hand.
flavorText: Father of Rexxar, Champion of the Horde, and Flexxar, Champion of the Gym.

name: Best in Shell
text: Tradeable Summon two 2/7 Turtles with Taunt.
flavorText: The agility course takes a while.

name: Big Game Hunter
text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion with 7 or more Attack.
flavorText: Mere devilsaurs no longer excite him. Soon he'll be trying to catch Onyxia with only a dull Krol Blade.

name: Blackjack Stunner
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, return a minion to its owner's hand. It costs (1) more.
flavorText: "I'm about to ruin this 10-cost minion's whole career."

name: Blacksmithing Hammer
text: Tradeable After you Trade this, gain +2 Durability.
flavorText: Passed through the hands of countless smiths, and eventually the skulls of their enemies.

name: Blackwater Cutlass
text: Tradeable After you Trade this, reduce the cost of a spell in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Popular around Stormwind for slashing prices.

name: Bladed Cultist
text: Combo: Gain +1/+1.
flavorText: He has a poor understanding of the law of diminishing returns.

name: Bladed Lady
text: Rush Costs (1) if your hero has 6 or more Attack.
flavorText: While you were busy learning magic, she studied the blade.

name: Blademaster Samuro
text: Rush Frenzy: Deal damage equal to this minion's Attack to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Artists paint their visions meticulously on canvas. Blademasters paint with, uh, broader strokes.

name: Bladestorm
text: Deal 1 damage to all minions. Repeat until one dies.
flavorText: Dear minions: Woosh, woosh, woosh, woosh, woosh. Best regards, Bladestorm

name: Blessed Goods
text: Discover a Secret, weapon, or Divine Shield minion.
flavorText: Guaranteed to contain no haunted dolls, cursed rings, or corrupted runeblades, or your money back.

name: Blessing of Authority
text: Give a minion +8/+8. It can't attack heroes this turn.
flavorText: A paladin fights with honor! We don't go face... until next turn!

name: Blessing of Kings
text: Give a minion +4/+4. (+4 Attack/+4 Health)
flavorText: Given the number of kings who have been assassinated, are you sure you want their blessing?

name: Blistering Rot
text: At the end of your turn, summon a Rot with stats equal to this minion's.
flavorText: Known as 'Fel Gel' to the Illidari, it's excellent protection against harsh Draenic sunshine.

name: Bloated Python
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 4/4 Hapless Handler.
flavorText: This is why Scholomance engineering students prefer C++.

name: Blood Herald
text: Whenever a friendly minion dies while this is in your hand, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: "Red Blood, it gives you wings."

name: Blood Shard Bristleback
text: Lifesteal. Battlecry: If your deck contains 10 or fewer cards, deal 6 damage to a minion.
flavorText: I'm bringin' bristle back (Yeah) Those other minions don't know how to act (Yeah) I think it's special how these crystals crack (Yeah) So turn around and I'll give you a smack (Yeah) (Take 'em to the Barrens)

name: Blood of G'huun
text: Taunt At the end of your turn, summon a 5/5 copy of a minion in your deck.
flavorText: An attempted cure becomes disease, blooming and thriving as rot and decay.

name: Bloodboil Brute
text: Rush Costs (1) less for each damaged minion.
flavorText: Call Gurtogg a brute if you like, but no one else cares about the wounded like he does.

name: Bloodbound Imp
text: Whenever this attacks, deal 2 damage to your hero.
flavorText: ALWAYS read the terms and conditions.

name: Bloodmage Thalnos
text: Spell Damage +1 Deathrattle: Draw a card.
flavorText: He's in charge of the Annual Scarlet Monastery Blood Drive!

name: Bloodsail Deckhand
text: Battlecry: The next weapon you play costs (1) less.
flavorText: Piracy is technically a discount.

name: Bloodsail Raider
text: Battlecry: Gain Attack equal to the Attack of your weapon.
flavorText: "I only plunder on days that end in 'y'."

name: Bogbeam
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Costs (0) if you have at least 7 Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Some think the mysterious bright lights in the bog are alien invaders, others think they're just swamp gas. Turns out, it's just druids.

name: Boggspine Knuckles
text: After your hero attacks, transform your minions into random ones that cost (1) more.
flavorText: I would NOT want to put my hand in there. It's... SQUISHY.

name: Bogstrok Clacker
text: Battlecry: Transform adjacent minions into random minions that cost (1) more.
flavorText: This clacker's crackers for hacking slackers into whack attackers.

name: Bola Shot
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and 2 damage to its neighbors.
flavorText: On second thought, bolas aren't very good against flying worms.

name: Bolner Hammerbeak
text: After you play a Battlecry minion, repeat the first Battlecry played this turn.
flavorText: Show him how to do something once, and he can do it a thousand times. This turn.

name: Bonechewer Brawler
text: Taunt Whenever this minion takes damage, gain +2 Attack.
flavorText: When you get this swole, arrows are basically free acupuncture.

name: Bonechewer Raider
text: Battlecry: If there is a damaged minion, gain +1/+1 and Rush.
flavorText: And if that minion has a frisbee, LOOK OUT!

name: Bonechewer Vanguard
text: Taunt Whenever this minion takes damage, gain +2 Attack.
flavorText: She came here to taunt you and chew on bones, and she's all outta bones.

name: Boneweb Egg
text: Deathrattle: Summon two 2/1 Spiders. If you discard this, trigger its Deathrattle.
flavorText: Noblegarden is going to be really exciting this year!

name: Brain Freeze
text: Freeze a minion. Combo: Also deal 3 damage to it.
flavorText: "The professor called on me, and I totally froze!"

name: Brawl
text: Destroy all minions except one. (chosen randomly)
flavorText: Do you know the first rule of Brawl Club?

name: Brightwing
text: Battlecry: Add a random Legendary minion to your hand.
flavorText: Little faerie dragons are made of sugar and spice and maniacal vice.

name: Brilliant Macaw
text: Battlecry: Repeat the last Battlecry you played.
flavorText: He's been repeating the same shanty for a month. Four pirates walked the plank last week. Middle of the ocean, just walked right off.

name: Brittlebone Destroyer
text: Battlecry: If your hero's Health changed this turn, destroy a minion.
flavorText: Broke many a leg in drama class.

name: Bru'kan
text: Nature Spell Damage +3
flavorText: Bru'kan, his body weathered and weary, felt his time nearing its end. Teaching brave champions like Rokara gives him hope for a greater future.

name: Bulk Up
text: Give a random Taunt minion in your hand +1/+1 and copy it.
flavorText: "For breakfast I usually go for a couple of kodo steaks, 5 Plainstrider eggs and an ice-cold milk to wash it down… all raw."

name: Bulwark of Azzinoth
text: Whenever your hero would take damage, this loses 1 Durability instead.
flavorText: This plate turned shield you shall wield, praying its powers fel will serve you well.

name: Bumper Car
text: Rush Deathrattle: Add two 1/1 Riders with Rush to your hand.
flavorText: Subject: Re: Unsafe Rides? bump

name: Burning Blade Acolyte
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 5/8 Demonspawn with Taunt.
flavorText: Wields a disappointingly normal looking blade.

name: Burrowing Scorpid
text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage. If that kills the target, gain Stealth.
flavorText: It's a game of hide and go sting.

name: C'Thun, the Shattered
text: Start of Game: Break into pieces. Battlecry: Deal 30 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: My grandfather's deck has no useless cards!

name: Cabal Acolyte
text: Taunt Spellburst: Gain control of a random enemy minion with 2 or less Attack.
flavorText: How did he get to the top of his class? He pulled a few strings!

name: Cagematch Custodian
text: Battlecry: Draw a weapon.
flavorText: Cleans up after a dust up.

name: Cairne Bloodhoof
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 5/5 Baine Bloodhoof.
flavorText: Cairne was killed by Garrosh, so... don't put this guy in a Warrior deck. It's pretty insensitive.

name: Call of the Grave
text: Discover a Deathrattle minion. If you have enough Mana to play it, trigger its Deathrattle.
flavorText: Necromancy is motivational speaking for the dead.

name: Canal Slogger
text: Rush, Lifesteal Overload: (1)
flavorText: "Another Monday in the canals huh? What a slog."

name: Cannonmaster Smythe
text: Battlecry: Transform your Secrets into 3/3 Soldiers. They transform back when they die.
flavorText: "Smythe, it's been a real blast serving the Alliance with you."

name: Cargo Guard
text: At the end of your turn, gain 3 Armor.
flavorText: *Arrrrrmor

name: Cariel Roame
text: Rush, Divine Shield Whenever this attacks, reduce the Cost of Holy spells in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Cariel had pledged her honor to the Alliance, but when someone matching her long-lost sister's description was sighted at the Crossroads, Cariel did the unthinkable: she abandoned her post and set out across the Barrens.

name: Carnival Barker
text: Whenever you summon a 1-Health minion, give it +1/+2.
flavorText: The barking initially confused faire-goers, so he switched to words.

name: Carnival Clown
text: Taunt Battlecry: Summon 2 copies of this. Corrupt: Fill your board with copies.
flavorText: Send in the clowns!

name: Carousel Gryphon
text: Divine Shield Corrupt: Gain +3/+3 and Taunt.
flavorText: "When does this bird land in Stormwind? I've been flying for hours!"

name: Carrion Studies
text: Discover a Deathrattle minion. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: A good read but a little too much fluff.

name: Cascading Disaster
text: Destroy a random enemy minion. Corrupt: Destroy 2. Corrupt Again: Destroy 3.
flavorText: Please keep all hands, arms, feet and legs inside the ride until the monster comes to a complete stop.

name: Catacomb Guard
text: Lifesteal Battlecry: Deal damage equal to this minion's Attack to an enemy minion.
flavorText: A little dark down here. So much for "serving the Light."

name: Celestial Alignment
text: Set each player to 0 Mana Crystals. Set the Cost of cards in all hands and decks to (1).
flavorText: "Is my deck any good?" "I mean, if the stars align."

name: Celestial Ink Set
text: After you spend 5 Mana on spells, reduce the cost of a spell in your hand by (5). Lose 1 Durability.
flavorText: "Dear Mother, I have a lot of spells and burst in my hand. You should maybe run more armor and healing next time. Cordially, Your child"

name: Cenarion Ward
text: Gain 8 Armor. Summon a random 8-Cost minion.
flavorText: Don't ask about his right hand. He's still growing into it.

name: Cenarius
text: Choose One - Give your other minions +2/+2; or Summon two 2/2 Treants with Taunt.
flavorText: Yes, he's a demigod. No, he doesn't need to wear a shirt.

name: Ceremonial Maul
text: Spellburst: Summon a Student with Taunt and stats equal to the spell's Cost.
flavorText: For the most discerning of hall monitors.

name: Chain Lightning (Rank 1)
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion and a random adjacent one. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: Still better than receiving a chain letter.

name: Chaos Leech
text: Lifesteal. Deal 3 damage to a minion. Outcast: Deal 5 instead.
flavorText: Otherwise known as a nematode.

name: Chaos Nova
text: Deal 4 damage to all minions.
flavorText: Illin' Illidan laying down the damage, flinging out the chaos as far as he can manage.

name: Chaos Strike
text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. Draw a card.
flavorText: "What do we want?" "CHAOS!" "When do we want it?" "WHEN LEAST EXPECTED!"

name: Charged Call
text: Discover a -Cost minion and summon it. (Upgraded for each Overload card you played this game!)
flavorText: You have a collect call from "AL'AKIR, LORD OF AIR AND THE FOUR WINDS." Do you accept these charges?

name: Cheesemonger
text: Whenever your opponent casts a spell, add a random spell with the same Cost to your hand.
flavorText: Secretly, the Big Cheese of SI:7.

name: Chillwind Yeti
flavorText: He always dreamed of coming down from the mountains and opening a noodle shop, but he never got the nerve.

name: Circus Amalgam
text: Taunt This has all minion types.
flavorText: Who needs a petting zoo when you have all the creatures right here?!

name: Circus Medic
text: Battlecry: Restore 4 Health. Corrupt: Deal 4 damage instead.
flavorText: Just be careful not to mix this with any creepy eyeballs, tentacles, or dark whispers, and you'll be fine in the morning.

name: City Architect
text: Battlecry: Summon two 0/5 Castle Walls with Taunt.
flavorText: "Oh, wait, I had this turned the wrong way. This was supposed to be a tower."

name: City Tax
text: Tradeable Lifesteal. Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: "Look pal, I don't care what kind of legion you saved the world from, pay up or else."

name: Claw Machine
text: Rush. Deathrattle: Draw a minion and give it +3/+3.
flavorText: "I have been mrglrlglr… chosen!"

name: Cleric of An'she
text: Battlecry: If you've restored Health this turn, Discover a spell from your deck.
flavorText: When it's her turn to cook, she'll always go for a Light sear.

name: Cloak of Shadows
text: Give your hero Stealth for 1 turn.
flavorText: Only worthy emperors can see the cloak.

name: Clockwork Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each card in your opponent's hand.
flavorText: He and Mountain Giant don't get along.

name: Clumsy Courier
text: Battlecry: Cast the highest Cost spell from your hand.
flavorText: Not the nacho cheese!

name: Coerce
text: Destroy a damaged minion. Combo: Destroy any minion.
flavorText: "Give me your lunch money, or the sandwich gets it!"

name: Cogmaster
text: Has +2 Attack while you have a Mech.
flavorText: After a while, you don't see the cogs and sprockets. All you see is a robot, a spider tank, a deathray...

name: Coilfang Warlord
text: Rush Deathrattle: Summon a 5/9 Warlord with Taunt.
flavorText: Prepare for the staunch conch launch!

name: Cold Blood
text: Give a minion +2 Attack. Combo: +4 Attack instead.
flavorText: "I'm cold blooded, check it and see!"

name: Coldarra Drake
text: You can use your Hero Power any number of times.
flavorText: The Grand Tournament has a "No dragons allowed" policy, but it's rarely enforced.

name: Coldlight Seer
text: Battlecry: Give your other Murlocs +2 Health.
flavorText: The Coldlight murlocs reside in the darkest pits of the Abyssal Depths. So no, there's no getting away from murlocs.

name: Combustion
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. Any excess damages both neighbors.
flavorText: Sally is friends with three Silverhand Recruits conveniently standing in a line. After casting this spell, how many friends does she have left? (Show your work.)

name: Command the Elements
text: Questline: Play 3 cards with Overload. Reward: Unlock your Overloaded Mana Crystals.
flavorText: What, you expected a shaman to have trouble with a place called STORMWIND?

name: Commencement
text: Summon a minion from your deck. Give it Taunt and Divine Shield.
flavorText: "Remember, graduates—you carry a heavy weight on your shoulders now."

name: Composting
text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Draw a card."
flavorText: The Treants really give their bodies to the cause.

name: Condemn (Rank 1)
text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: "I wished you no harm, but for your cruelty, by the light, I condemn you all!" Xyrella shouted, unaware that irony was not her strong suit.

name: Conditioning (Rank 1)
text: Give minions in your hand +1/+1. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: Now drop and give me 5 Mana.

name: Cone of Cold
text: Freeze a minion and the minions next to it, and deal 1 damage to them.
flavorText: Magi of the Kirin Tor were casting Cubes of Cold for many years before Cones came into fashion some 90 years ago.

name: Confection Cyclone
text: Battlecry: Add two 1/2 Sugar Elementals to your hand.
flavorText: "Oh, I thought it was a desert elemental?"

name: Conjure Mana Biscuit
text: Add a Biscuit to your hand that refreshes 2 Mana Crystals.
flavorText: So THIS is why she was AFK.

name: Consecration
text: Deal 2 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: Consecrated ground glows with Holy energy. But it smells a little, too.

name: Conviction (Rank 1)
text: Give a random friendly minion +3 Attack. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: It was the strength of Cariel's faith that emboldened the defenders of Northwatch that day. Although the strength of her giant hammer didn’t exactly hurt either.

name: Cookie the Cook
text: Lifesteal Deathrattle: Equip a 2/3 Stirring Rod with Lifesteal.
flavorText: Unsurprisingly, "Seafood Surprise" was no one's favorite dish.

name: Coordinated Strike
text: Summon three 1/1 Illidari with Rush.
flavorText: Undisputed champions of "Dancing with the Satyrs."

name: Copycat
text: Battlecry: Add a copy of the next card your opponent plays to your hand.
flavorText: Whatever you do, DON’T let two of them meet.

name: Cornelius Roame
text: At the start and end of each player's turn, draw a card.
flavorText: Raised two perfectly normal daughters. Then one died and brought doom to Stormwind.

name: Corsair Cache
text: Draw a weapon. Give it +1 Durability.
flavorText: Where's a corsair's favorite place to hide treasure? Under their deck!

name: Costumed Entertainer
text: Battlecry: Give a random minion in your hand +2/+2.
flavorText: Just remember not to talk. It breaks character.

name: Counterfeit Blade
text: Battlecry: Gain a random friendly Deathrattle that triggered this game.
flavorText: Don't worry, the blade retracts into the handle!

name: Counterspell
text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, Counter it.
flavorText: What's the difference between a mage playing with Counterspell and a mage who isn't? The mage who isn't is getting Pyroblasted in the face.

name: Cowardly Grunt
text: Deathrattle: Summon a minion from your deck.
flavorText: Cowardice is the wisest part of valor.

name: Crabrider
text: Rush Battlecry: Gain Windfury this turn only.
flavorText: "Now I'm falling asleep and she's calling a crab…"

name: Cram Session
text: Draw 1 (card, cards) (improved by Spell Damage).
flavorText: The font of the arcane gives nearly limitless access to power and energy! But it can't keep you awake, for that we still use coffee.

name: Crazed Alchemist
text: Battlecry: Swap the Attack and Health of a minion.
flavorText: "You'll love my new recipe!" he says... especially if you're not happy with your current number of limbs.

name: Crimson Clergy
text: After a friendly character is healed, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: He won't drop the ball.

name: Crimson Hothead
text: Spellburst: Gain +1 Attack and Taunt.
flavorText: Has a real passion for spelling.

name: Crimson Sigil Runner
text: Outcast: Draw a card.
flavorText: He's not the fastest of the bunch, but he'll take a stab at it anyway.

name: Crimson Sigil Runner
text: Outcast: Draw a card.
flavorText: He's not the fastest of the bunch, but he'll take a stab at it anyway.

name: Crossroads Gossiper
text: After a friendly Secret is revealed, gain +2/+2.
flavorText: Not afraid to spill the tea.

name: Crossroads Watch Post
text: Can't attack. Whenever your opponent casts a spell, give your minions +1/+1.
flavorText: All of Barrens Chat is recorded and kept on thousands of scrolls stored beneath this tower.

name: Crow's Nest Lookout
text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to the left and right-most enemy minions.
flavorText: The extra eyes means he sees extra good.

name: Cruel Taskmaster
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it +2 Attack.
flavorText: "I'm going to need you to come in on Sunday." - Cruel Taskmaster

name: Cult Neophyte
text: Battlecry: Your opponent's spells cost (1) more next turn.
flavorText: Make a new recruit's deficiencies your efficiencies.

name: Cursed Vagrant
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 7/5 Shadow with Stealth.
flavorText: Little did he know… it was really the talbuk leg that was cursed.

name: Cutting Class
text: Draw 2 cards. Costs (1) less per Attack of your weapon.
flavorText: When you actually are the sharpest tool in the shed.

name: Cycle of Hatred
text: Deal 3 damage to all minions. Summon a 3/3 Spirit for every minion killed.
flavorText: If you run 2 of these, would that make it the bi-cycle of hatred?

name: Dancing Cobra
text: Corrupt: Gain Poisonous.
flavorText: Snakes are just tentacles with fangs.

name: Dark Alley Pact
text: Summon a Fiend with stats equal to your hand size.
flavorText: "With your help, I can finally install some proper lighting in this alley."

name: Dark Inquisitor Xanesh
text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of all Corrupt and Corrupted cards in your hand and deck by (2).
flavorText: Fear is the mind-killer, and also the name of my wurm.

name: Dark Iron Dwarf
text: Battlecry: Give a minion +2 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Guardians of Dark Iron Ore. Perhaps the most annoying ore, given where you have to forge it.

name: Darkbishop Benedictus
text: Start of Game: If the spells in your deck are all Shadow, enter Shadowform.
flavorText: Dark Bishop takes Light Pawn, check.

name: Darkglare
text: After your hero takes damage, refresh a Mana Crystal.
flavorText: He's got a dark glare, but he sees crystal clear!

name: Darkmoon Dirigible
text: Divine Shield Corrupt: Gain Rush.
flavorText: "It's dirigible? I don’t even know what diriging is!"

name: Darkmoon Rabbit
text: Rush, Poisonous Also damages the minions next to whomever this attacks.
flavorText: That's no ordinary rabbit! That's the most foul, cruel, and bad-tempered rodent you ever set eyes on!

name: Darkmoon Statue
text: Your other minions have +1 Attack. Corrupt: This gains +4 Attack.
flavorText: As far as workplace injuries go, Silas is protected by his statue of limitations.

name: Darkmoon Tonk
text: Deathrattle: Fire four missiles at random enemies that deal 2 damage each.
flavorText: "Ready to roll out!"

name: Darkspear Berserker
text: Deathrattle: Deal 5 damage to your hero.
flavorText: "If I die, I'm taking my hero down with me."

name: Day at the Faire
text: Summon 3 Silver Hand Recruits. Corrupt: Summon 5.
flavorText: Karl knew he would someday regret that turkey leg.

name: Deadly Poison
text: Give your weapon +2 Attack.
flavorText: Rogues guard the secrets to poison-making carefully, lest magi start incorporating poison into their spells. Poisonbolt? Rain of Poison? Poison Elemental? Nobody wants that.

name: Deadly Shot
text: Destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: Our ballista operator is effective, but not picky.

name: Death Speaker Blackthorn
text: Battlecry: Summon 3 Deathrattle minions that cost (5) or less from your deck.
flavorText: He can speak death but has a hard time reading it.

name: Death's Head Cultist
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Restore 4 Health to your hero.
flavorText: Nothing can stop death. Except a Taunt. With Healing.

name: Deathmatch Pavilion
text: Summon a 3/2 Duelist. If your hero attacked this turn, summon another.
flavorText: Worth it for the stuffed toy at the end.

name: Deathwarden
text: Deathrattles can't trigger.
flavorText: Ride or die takes on a new meaning.

name: Deathwing the Destroyer
text: Battlecry: Destroy all other minions. Discard a card for each destroyed.
flavorText: "He’s Deathwing? That one's Deathwing? You're Deathwing!? I'm DEATHWING! ARE THERE ANY OTHER DEATHWINGS I SHOULD KNOW ABOUT?"

name: Deck of Chaos
text: Swap the Cost and Attack of all minions in your deck.
flavorText: Yeah, it's chaos, but it's organized chaos.

name: Deck of Lunacy
text: Transform spells in your deck into ones that cost (3) more. (They keep their original Cost.)
flavorText: Voted "Most Lunacy" in Madness Monthly magazine.

name: Deep Freeze
text: Freeze an enemy. Summon two 3/6 Water Elementals.
flavorText: "Dancing with the Satyrs… on Ice!"

name: Deeprun Engineer
text: Battlecry: Discover a Mech. It costs (1) less.
flavorText: Deeprun Tram instructions: 300,000 pieces, 600,000 steps.

name: Deepwater Evoker
text: Battlecry: Draw a spell. Gain Armor equal to its Cost.
flavorText: "Cap'n! We've hit an iceberg! ...No, it’s not my fault!"

name: Defend the Dwarven District
text: Questline: Deal damage with 2 spells. Reward: Your Hero Power can target minions.
flavorText: Don't shoot until you see the purples of their eyes.

name: Defender of Argus
text: Battlecry: Give adjacent minions +1/+1 and Taunt.
flavorText: You wouldn’t think that Argus would need this much defending. But it does.

name: Defias Blastfisher
text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to a random enemy. Repeat for each of your Beasts.
flavorText: She's a dynamite fishing trainer.

name: Defias Cannoneer
text: After your hero attacks, deal 2 damage to a random enemy twice.
flavorText: "... three."

name: Defias Leper
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Shadow spell, deal 2 damage.
flavorText: Do NOT eat Cookie’s Seafood Surprise.

name: Demon Companion
text: Summon a random Demon Companion.
flavorText: Owning a pet can be real hell at times.

name: Demonic Assault
text: Deal 3 damage. Summon two 1/3 Voidwalkers with Taunt.
flavorText: Right next to the demonic pepper.

name: Demonic Studies
text: Discover a Demon. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: "Do you wanna summon a demon? I wanna summon a demon!"

name: Derailed Coaster
text: Battlecry: Summon a 1/1 Rider with Rush for each minion in your hand.
flavorText: So long as it doesn’t kill you, it's considered part of the ride "experience."

name: Desk Imp
flavorText: "I feel inky!"

name: Desperate Prayer
text: Restore 5 Health to each hero.
flavorText: Woah, we're halfway there, woah oh...

name: Deviate Dreadfang
text: After you cast a Nature spell, summon a 4/2 Viper with Rush.
flavorText: Even with wings, snakes STILL don't have legs.

name: Devolving Missiles
text: Shoot three missiles at random enemy minions that transform them into ones that cost (1) less.
flavorText: Most intermural spell-dueling contests end with a field of wisps.

name: Devouring Ectoplasm
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 2/2 Adventurer with a random bonus effect.
flavorText: When it's on keto, it only devours tauren.

name: Devouring Plague
text: Lifesteal. Deal 4 damage randomly split among all enemy minions.
flavorText: "How’d we miss this one in Uldum?" —Rafaam

name: Devouring Swarm
text: Choose an enemy minion. Your minions attack it, then return any that die to your hand.
flavorText: Collect… essence.

name: Devout Dungeoneer
text: Battlecry: Draw a spell. If it's a Holy spell, reduce its Cost by (2).
flavorText: "Please do smaller pulls, this is my first time healing."

name: Devout Pupil
text: Divine Shield, Taunt Costs (1) less for each spell you've cast on friendly characters this game.
flavorText: He considers textbooks Light reading.

name: Diligent Notetaker
text: Spellburst: Return the spell to your hand.
flavorText: You never know what cards are going to be on the test.

name: Dire Frenzy
text: Give a Beast +3/+3. Shuffle 3 copies into your deck with +3/+3.
flavorText: It's always Huffer. And Huffer. And Huffer. And Huffer.

name: Dire Wolf Alpha
text: Adjacent minions have +1 Attack.
flavorText: We are pretty excited about the upcoming release of Dire Wolf Beta, just repost this sign for a chance at a key.

name: Dirty Tricks
text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, draw 2 cards.
flavorText: "Ahh sand in my eyes! Also, I'm being stabbed."

name: Disciplinarian Gandling
text: After you play a minion, destroy it and summon a 4/4 Failed Student.
flavorText: "He doesn’t grade on a curve, but on a sharp spike instead."

name: Disguised Wanderer
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 9/1 Inquisitor.
flavorText: He wanders east... always into the east.

name: Divine Rager
text: Divine Shield
flavorText: For when you need to rage, rage against the dying of the Light.

name: Doctor Krastinov
text: Rush Whenever this attacks, give your weapon +1/+1.
flavorText: He is not a medical doctor.

name: Doggie Biscuit
text: Tradeable Give a minion +2/+3. After you Trade this, give a friendly minion Rush.
flavorText: Reserved for Edwin’s favorite lapdogs.

name: Don't Feed the Animals
text: Give all Beasts in your hand +1/+1. Corrupt: Give them +2/+2 instead.
flavorText: They're still cleaning up the mess from the last time someone fed the basilisk a deep fried candybar.

name: Doomhammer
text: Windfury, Overload: (2)
flavorText: Orgrim Doomhammer gave this legendary weapon to Thrall. His name is a total coincidence.

name: Double Jump
text: Draw an Outcast card from your deck.
flavorText: The key to every speed run.

name: Draconic Studies
text: Discover a Dragon. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: Our Draconic Studies program has a high rate of burnout.

name: Draenei Totemcarver
text: Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each friendly Totem.
flavorText: It's nice to find a real craftsman in this day and age of mass-produced totems.

name: Dragonmaw Overseer
text: At the end of your turn, give another friendly minion +2/+2.
flavorText: Ah, the Booterang... nothing cures peon laziness faster.

name: Dragonmaw Sentinel
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, gain +1 Attack and Lifesteal.
flavorText: On the side, she's training for the annual Dragonmaw hammer throw tournament.

name: Dragonmaw Sky Stalker
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 3/4 Dragonrider.
flavorText: "I will find you, sky!"

name: Drain Soul
text: Lifesteal Deal 3 damage to a minion.
flavorText: Cleans even the toughest clogs with just a flick of the wrist!

name: Dread Infernal
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to ALL other characters.
flavorText: "INFERNOOOOOOOOOO!" - Jaraxxus, Eredar Lord of the Burning Legion

name: Dreaded Mount
text: Give a minion +1/+1. When it dies, summon an endless Dreadsteed.
flavorText: This is the summoning that never ends, and it goes on and on my friends...

name: Dreadlord's Bite
text: Outcast: Deal 1 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: When it gets too dull, it's more of a nibble.

name: Dreaming Drake
text: Taunt Corrupt: Gain +2/+2.
flavorText: Some dragons dream of conquering Azeroth, some just dream of being 5/6s.

name: Druid of the Claw
text: Choose One - Transform into a 5/4 with Rush; or a 5/6 with Taunt.
flavorText: Cat or Bear? Cat or Bear?! I just cannot CHOOSE!

name: Druid of the Plains
text: Rush Frenzy: Transform into a 6/7 Kodo with Taunt.
flavorText: Not to be confused with the aeronautically advanced Druid of the Planes.

name: Druid of the Reef
text: Choose One - Transform into a 3/1 Shark with Rush; or a 1/3 Turtle with Taunt.
flavorText: “Wow, there’s a whole sunken city down here!”

name: Dunk Tank
text: Deal 4 damage. Corrupt: Then deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: "When I said bring a tank to the dungeon, this is not what I had in mind!"

name: E.T.C., God of Metal
text: After a friendly Rush minion attacks, deal 2 damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: There are Old Gods and then there are Rock Gods.

name: Earth Elemental
text: Taunt Overload: (2)
flavorText: Nothing beats rock.

name: Earth Revenant
text: Taunt Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Have you guys seen a pair of rock legs lying around anywhere?

name: Earthen Ring Farseer
text: Battlecry: Restore 3 Health.
flavorText: He can see really far, and he doesn't use a telescope like those filthy pirates.

name: Educated Elekk
text: Whenever a spell is played, this minion remembers it. Deathrattle: Shuffle the spells into your deck.
flavorText: "This reminds me of a saying. 'An elekk never…' something. I can't remember."

name: Edwin, Defias Kingpin
text: Battlecry: Draw a card. If you play it this turn, gain +2/+2 and repeat this effect.
flavorText: He’s not going to tear down the walls of Stormwind sitting around in the Hall of Fame.

name: Efficient Octo-bot
text: Frenzy: Reduce the cost of cards in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Pull the lever, Octo-bot... Wrong leverrrrr!

name: Elekk Mount
text: Give a minion +4/+7 and Taunt. When it dies, summon an Elekk.
flavorText: Pink Elekks are on parade!

name: Elven Archer
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage.
flavorText: Don't bother asking her out on a date. She'll shoot you down.

name: Elwynn Boar
text: Deathrattle: If you had 7 Elwynn Boars die this game, equip a 15/3 Sword of a Thousand Truths. ( /7)
flavorText: Be grateful we lowered the requirement from 65,340,285.

name: Emerald Skytalon
text: Rush
flavorText: Sworn protectors of Ysera at the Emerald Dragonshrine, these majestic owls have been touched by the powers of the Emerald Dream, taking on an almost crystalline appearance.

name: Enchanted Cauldron
text: Spellburst: Cast a random spell of the same Cost.
flavorText: Do you smell what the cauldron is cooking? If so, we apologize.

name: Enchanted Raven
flavorText: Once upon a midnight restive, Medivh pondered, feeling festive!

name: Encumbered Pack Mule
text: Taunt When you draw this, add a copy of it to your hand.
flavorText: "Now I can pick up EVERY knick-knack."

name: Enhanced Dreadlord
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon a 5/5 Dreadlord with Lifesteal.
flavorText: Photo actually taken across the street in the reflection of a doorknob.

name: Enslaved Fel Lord
text: Taunt. Also damages the minions next to whomever this attacks.
flavorText: He's not really chained up. He just wears that to scare the imps when they get too unruly.

name: Enthusiastic Banker
text: At the end of your turn, store a card from your deck. Deathrattle: Add the stored cards to your hand.
flavorText: She offers 0% interest.

name: Entitled Customer
text: Battlecry: Deal damage equal to your hand size to all other minions.
flavorText: "Do you have any idea how much mana I've spent at your store? 6."

name: Entrapped Sorceress
text: Battlecry: If you control a Quest, Discover a spell.
flavorText: "If you're a city guard, you have to tell me. Otherwise, it's entrapment."

name: Envoy Rustwix
text: Deathrattle: Shuffle 3 random Prime Legendary minions into your deck.
flavorText: "Time to roll. Rusted Legion, ho!"

name: Equality
text: Change the Health of ALL minions to 1.
flavorText: We are all special unique snowflakes... with 1 Health.

name: Ethereal Augmerchant
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Spell Damage +1.
flavorText: According to him, undamaged minions just spell problems.

name: Ethereal Conjurer
text: Battlecry: Discover a spell.
flavorText: Despite the name, he's a solid conjurer.

name: Evocation
text: Fill your hand with random Mage spells. At the end of your turn, discard them.
flavorText: You too could be the winner of the national spelling spree!

name: Execute
text: Destroy a damaged enemy minion.
flavorText: It's okay, he deserved it.

name: Expendable Performers
text: Summon seven 1/1 Illidari with Rush. If they all die this turn, summon seven more.
flavorText: When someone gets injured, it's considered performance art.

name: Explosive Sheep
text: Deathrattle: Deal 2 damage to all minions.
flavorText: How is this supposed to work? Your enemies think, "Hey! Cute sheep!" and run over to cuddle it?

name: Explosive Trap
text: Secret: When your hero is attacked, deal 2 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: It traps your food AND cooks it for you!

name: Eye Beam
text: Lifesteal. Deal 3 damage to a minion. Outcast: This costs (1).
flavorText: Sometimes looks CAN kill.

name: Faceless Manipulator
text: Battlecry: Choose a minion and become a copy of it.
flavorText: The Faceless Ones are servants of Yogg-Saron, and they feed on fear. Right now they are feeding on your fear of accidentally disenchanting all your good cards.

name: Faire Arborist
text: Choose One - Draw a card; or Summon a 2/2 Treant. Corrupt: Do both.
flavorText: The bad apple never falls far from the treant.

name: Fairground Fool
text: Taunt Corrupt: Gain +4 Health.
flavorText: "What did Illidan say when his rocketeer broke down on the Darkmoon racetrack? YOU ARE NOT REPAIRED!"

name: Fallen Hero
text: Your Hero Power deals 1 extra damage.
flavorText: And he can't get up.

name: Fangbound Druid
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Reduce the Cost of a Beast in your hand by (2).
flavorText: Bound by the law of the fang, these druid floss their teeth twice a day.

name: Fantastic Firebird
text: Windfury
flavorText: The original flaming chicken.

name: Far Watch Post
text: Can't attack. After your opponent draws a card, it costs (1) more (up to 10).
flavorText: Dabu, man. Like, far out.

name: Feast of Souls
text: Draw a card for each friendly minion that died this turn.
flavorText: Nothing fills you up like soul food!

name: Feat of Strength
text: Give a random Taunt minion in your hand +5/+5.
flavorText: Generally happens right after the airing of grievances.

name: Fel Barrage
text: Deal 2 damage to the lowest Health enemy, twice.
flavorText: Kurtrus leapt over a tombstone towards the demonic invaders, yelling "PEW! PEW!" as he shot them down with fel magic.

name: Fel Guardians
text: Summon three 1/2 Demons with Taunt. Costs (1) less whenever a friendly minion dies.
flavorText: What happened after the guardians tripped? They Fel.

name: Fel Summoner
text: Deathrattle: Summon a random Demon from your hand.
flavorText: All's well that ends fel when the fel summoner summons well.

name: Felfin Navigator
text: Battlecry: Give your other Murlocs +1/+1.
flavorText: Return my fishes to me, and I myself shall carry you to the gates of Mrrhalla!

name: Felfire Deadeye
text: Your Hero Power costs (1) less.
flavorText: She only shoots people who pet her cat without asking first.

name: Felgorger
text: Battlecry: Draw a Fel spell. Reduce its Cost by (2).
flavorText: The 'everything green' diet.

name: Felosophy
text: Copy the lowest Cost Demon in your hand. Outcast: Give both +1/+1.
flavorText: "Like, isn't evil subjective man?"

name: Felrattler
text: Rush Deathrattle: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: It only rattles when YOU'RE in danger.

name: Felsaber
text: Can only attack if your hero attacked this turn.
flavorText: Some drivers rev their engines. This one growls all on its own.

name: Felscream Blast
text: Lifesteal. Deal 1 damage to a minion and its neighbors.
flavorText: All the souls start running when they see the felscream truck.

name: Felsoul Jailer
text: Battlecry: Your opponent discards a minion. Deathrattle: Return it.
flavorText: He can lock 'em up, but he just can't keep 'em.

name: Felsteel Executioner
text: Corrupt: Become a weapon.
flavorText: "My mom said I could be anything I want."

name: Feral Rage
text: Choose One - Give your hero +4 Attack this turn; or Gain 8 Armor.
flavorText: Let's be honest. One option is a lot ragier than the other.

name: Feral Spirit
text: Summon two 2/3 Spirit Wolves with Taunt. Overload: (1)
flavorText: Spirit wolves are like regular wolves with pom-poms.

name: Field Contact
text: After you play a Battlecry or Combo card, draw a card.
flavorText: That's not a knife... THIS is a knife!

name: Fiendish Circle
text: Summon four 1/1 Imps.
flavorText: Like a knitting circle, but less evil.

name: Fiery War Axe
flavorText: During times of tranquility and harmony, this weapon was called by its less popular name, Chilly Peace Axe.

name: Final Gasp
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If it dies, summon a 2/2 Adventurer with a random bonus effect.
flavorText: And with a raspy whisper, he uttered his final words, "rez plz."

name: Final Showdown
text: Questline: Draw 4 cards in one turn. Reward: Reduce the Cost of the cards drawn by (1).
flavorText: Finally. The last Hearthstone card.

name: Find the Imposter
text: Questline: Play 2 SI:7 cards. Reward: Add a Spy Gizmo to your hand.
flavorText: My money is on the evil advisor to the king.

name: Fire Breather
text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to all minions except Demons.
flavorText: "Phew! That skull has been stuck between my teeth for hours!"

name: Fire Elemental
text: Battlecry: Deal 4 damage.
flavorText: He can never take a bath. Ewww.

name: Fire Sale
text: Tradeable Deal 3 damage to all minions.
flavorText: Everything is 50% off now that our warehouse burned down.

name: Fireball
text: Deal 6 damage.
flavorText: This spell is useful for burning things. If you're looking for spells that toast things, or just warm them a little, you're in the wrong place.

name: Firebrand
text: Spellburst: Deal 4 damage randomly split among all enemy minions.
flavorText: Too cool for school, too hot for thought.

name: Firemancer Flurgl
text: After you play a Murloc, deal 1 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: Diss tracks spitting straight fire.

name: Firework Elemental
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Corrupt: Deal 12 instead.
flavorText: The brightest spark can still go dark.

name: First Blade of Wrynn
text: Divine Shield Battlecry: Gain Rush if this has at least 4 Attack.
flavorText: Valedictorian of knight school.

name: First Day of School
text: Add 2 random 1-Cost minions to your hand.
flavorText: "Report to the bookstore to buy your books, the alchemist to buy your potions, and then get your wands at the… wandryroom?"

name: First Flame
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. Add a Second Flame to your hand.
flavorText: You never forget your first love: fire.

name: Fishy Flyer
text: Rush. Deathrattle: Add a 4/3 Ghost with Rush to your hand.
flavorText: Like a fish out of water.

name: Fizzy Elemental
text: Rush Taunt
flavorText: Loved. Hated. Carbonated.

name: Flame Imp
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to your hero.
flavorText: Imps like being on fire. They just do.

name: Flamestrike
text: Deal 5 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: When the ground is on fire, you should not stop, drop, and roll.

name: Flash Heal
text: Restore 5 Health.
flavorText: Flash! Ahhhhhhh~

name: Fleethoof Pearltusk
text: Rush Corrupt: Gain +4/+4.
flavorText: Guest interactions may vary over the duration of the visit.

name: Flesh Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each time your hero's Health changed during your turns.
flavorText: "A BIG mistake."

name: Flesheating Ghoul
text: Whenever a minion dies, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: 'Flesheating' is an unfair name. It's just that there's not really much else for him to eat.

name: Flightmaster Dungar
text: Battlecry: Choose a flightpath and go Dormant. Awaken with a bonus when you complete it!
flavorText: Flight’s a little bumpy, but there’s plenty of legroom.

name: Floecaster
text: Costs (2) less for each Frozen enemy.
flavorText: His real name is Melvin, but he prefers his friends call him ... <sigh> ..."Floecaster."

name: Florist
text: At the end of your turn, reduce the cost of a Nature spell in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Trade district. Trade district a shop. Color Legendary. Color Legendary golden. Rose is a rose is a rose is a rose.

name: Flurry (Rank 1)
text: Freeze a random enemy minion. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: Flurry, Flurrier, Flurriest.

name: Focused Will
text: Silence a minion, then give it +3 Health.
flavorText: Extreme focus is almost as effective as a really flashy distraction.

name: Fogsail Freebooter
text: Battlecry: If you have a weapon equipped, deal 2 damage.
flavorText: Goes cheap on wardrobe so he can spend on weaponry.

name: Font of Power
text: Discover a Mage minion. If your deck has no minions, keep all 3.
flavorText: It's Comic Sans.

name: Force of Nature
text: Summon three 2/2 Treants.
flavorText: "I think I'll just nap under these trees. Wait... AAAAAHHH!" - Blinkfizz, the Unfortunate Gnome

name: Forest Warden Omu
text: Spellburst: Refresh your Mana Crystals.
flavorText: She wishes all things could grow and flourish at Scholomance. If only she knew…

name: Fortune Teller
text: Taunt Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each spell in your hand.
flavorText: "I see a giant piano in your future."

name: Foxy Fraud
text: Battlecry: Your next Combo card this turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: His other street con involves a druid. He can't pull it off without a plant.

name: Frazzled Freshman
flavorText: "Late to bed, early to rise, makes a student unable to open her eyes."

name: Free Admission
text: Draw 2 minions. If they're both Demons, reduce their Costs by (2).
flavorText: "Quick, get in before someone sees you, or worse, someone sees me."

name: Freezing Trap
text: Secret: When an enemy minion attacks, return it to its owner's hand. It costs (2) more.
flavorText: "Dang, that's cold." - appropriate response to Freezing Trap, or a mean joke.

name: Frostweave Dungeoneer
text: Battlecry: Draw a spell. If it's a Frost spell, summon two 1/1 Elementals that Freeze.
flavorText: It's a woven blanket of ice but surprisingly comforting.

name: Frothing Berserker
text: Whenever a minion takes damage, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: He used to work as an accountant before he tried his hand at Berserkering.

name: Frozen Shadoweaver
text: Battlecry: Freeze an enemy.
flavorText: She still wears her Frozen Shadoweave set despite the many, many nerfs. She just can't let it go!

name: Fungal Fortunes
text: Draw 3 cards. Discard any minions drawn.
flavorText: Far superior to a beanstalk boondoggle.

name: Furious Felfin
text: Battlecry: If your hero attacked this turn, gain +1 Attack and Rush.
flavorText: Signature moves include Eye Bream, Feast of Soles, and Metamorphofish.

name: Fury (Rank 1)
text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: Rank 3 is when your mom uses your middle name.

name: G'huun the Blood God
text: Battlecry: Draw 2 cards. They cost Health instead of Mana.
flavorText: All of the other Old Gods used to laugh and call him names. They never let poor G'huun join in any Old God games.

name: Gadgetzan Auctioneer
text: Whenever you cast a spell, draw a card.
flavorText: He used to run the black market auction house, but there was just too much violence and he had to move.

name: Galloping Savior
text: Secret: After your opponent plays three cards in a turn, summon a 3/4 Steed with Taunt.
flavorText: "Look to my coming on the first light of the third card."

name: Game Master
text: The first Secret you play each turn costs (1).
flavorText: "You hear the mrgrgls of angry murlocs approaching. Roll initiative!"

name: Gan'arg Glaivesmith
text: Outcast: Give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: When isolation becomes motivation.

name: Garrote
text: Deal 2 damage to the enemy hero. Shuffle 3 Bleeds into your deck that deal 2 more when drawn.
flavorText: "I don't have money… but what I do have is a particular set of skills."

name: Germination
text: Summon a copy of a friendly minion. Give the copy Taunt.
flavorText: I regret asking how sporelings are made.

name: Gibberling
text: Spellburst: Summon a Gibberling.
flavorText: "As a Linguistics student I have studied the Gibberlings. I have determined they are speaking Gibberish."

name: Gift of Luminance
text: Give a minion Divine Shield, then summon a 1/1 copy of it.
flavorText: You get a small version of yourself in a snow globe to remember the moment.

name: Glacier Racer
text: Spellburst: Deal 3 damage to all Frozen enemies.
flavorText: It’s just not the same without a super suit.

name: Glide
text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Draw 4 cards. Outcast: Your opponent does the same.
flavorText: "Come with me, and you'll see, a whole new hand of possibly the same cards."

name: Glowfly Swarm
text: Summon a 2/2 Glowfly for each spell in your hand.
flavorText: Glowflies are distant relations to spelling bees.

name: Golakka Glutton
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Beast and gain +1/+1.
flavorText: We lost our last cook to one of these.

name: Gold Road Grunt
text: Taunt Frenzy: Gain Armor equal to the damage taken.
flavorText: No, no, no, Gold Roads are very different from Yellow Brick Roads.

name: Goldshire Gnoll
text: Rush Costs (1) less for each other card in your hand.
flavorText: They're searching for one ring. They're pretty sure someone said Goldshire.

name: Goliath, Sneed's Masterpiece
text: Battlecry: Fire five rockets at enemy minions that deal 2 damage each. (You pick the targets!)
flavorText: “Listen, this baby has blades, rockets, and rocket blades. Only thing it doesn’t have is good gas mileage.”

name: Goody Two-Shields
text: Divine Shield Spellburst: Gain Divine Shield.
flavorText: These are my shields. There are at least two like them, and both are mine.

name: Gorehowl
text: Attacking a minion costs 1 Attack instead of 1 Durability.
flavorText: Grommash Hellscream's famous axe. Somehow this ended up in Prince Malchezaar's possession. Quite the mystery!

name: Grand Empress Shek'zara
text: Battlecry: Discover a card in your deck and draw all copies of it.
flavorText: So is a Grand Empress an empress that's grand or an empress's empress?

name: Grand Finale
text: Summon an 8/8 Elemental. Repeat for each Elemental you played last turn.
flavorText: Considering all the other hazards at Darkmoon, overindulgent pyrotechnics seem downright pedestrian.

name: Grand Magus Antonidas
text: Battlecry: If you've cast a Fire spell on each of your last three turns, cast 3 Fireballs at random enemies. ( /3)
flavorText: He's really disappointed Jaina became a frost mage.

name: Grand Totem Eys'or
text: At the end of your turn, give +1/+1 to all other Totems in your hand, deck and battlefield.
flavorText: Some say it can see straight into the soul of any who dare to read its flavor text...

name: Granite Forgeborn
text: Battlecry: Reduce the cost of Elementals in your hand and deck by (1).
flavorText: If he stops being useful, just turn him into a kitchen countertop.

name: Grey Sage Parrot
text: Battlecry: Repeat the last spell you've cast that costs (5) or more.
flavorText: Nothing is more terrifying than a parrot squawking "Pyroblast!"

name: Greybough
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Give a random friendly minion "Deathrattle: Summon Greybough."
flavorText: The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The next best time is when you lose a minion.

name: Greyheart Sage
text: Battlecry: If you control a Stealthed minion, draw 2 cards.
flavorText: "What am I drinking again?"

name: Grim Necromancer
text: Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Skeletons.
flavorText: WARNING: Skeletons will NOT explode.

name: Grimoire of Sacrifice
text: Destroy a friendly minion. Deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: "What kind of bedtime story is this?"

name: Grommash Hellscream
text: Charge Has +6 Attack while damaged.
flavorText: Grommash drank the tainted blood of Mannoroth, dooming the orcs to green skin and red eyes! Maybe not his best decision.

name: Groundskeeper
text: Taunt Battlecry: If you're holding a spell that costs (5) or more, restore 5 Health.
flavorText: It’s tricky for dryads to tend the garden without trampling the flowers.

name: Gruntled Patron
text: Frenzy: Summon another Gruntled Patron.
flavorText: Gruntled and whelmed.

name: Guardian Animals
text: Summon two Beasts that cost (5) or less from your deck. Give them Rush.
flavorText: The guidelines specifically state: "Students may also bring an ironbeak owl OR an alleycat OR a toad." They never said how big.

name: Guardian Augmerchant
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Divine Shield.
flavorText: "What doesn't kill you makes me money!"

name: Guardian of Kings
text: Taunt Battlecry: Restore 6 Health to your hero.
flavorText: Holy beings from the beyond are so cliché!

name: Guess the Weight
text: Draw a card. Guess if your next card costs more or less to draw it.
flavorText: "And then at the last second, I'll shapeshift into cat form!"

name: Guff Runetotem
text: After you cast a Nature spell, give another friendly minion +2/+2.
flavorText: "By the twins above and twins below, our companions will lead us through." —Guff Runetotem

name: Guidance
text: Look at two spells. Add one to your hand or Overload: (1) to get both.
flavorText: Plainsrunning will result in disqualification.

name: Guild Trader
text: Tradeable Spell Damage +2
flavorText: Somehow, she manages six different professions.

name: Gurubashi Berserker
text: Whenever this minion takes damage, gain +3 Attack.
flavorText: No Pain, No Gain.

name: Gyreworm
text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, deal 3 damage.
flavorText: This game of ring toss just got really intense.

name: Hammer of the Naaru
text: Battlecry: Summon a 6/6 Holy Elemental with Taunt.
flavorText: The naaru wasn't using it. It doesn't have arms.

name: Hand of A'dal
text: Give a minion +2/+1. Draw a card.
flavorText: When it meets the Hand of Gul'dan, they're SHAKING.

name: Hand of Gul'dan
text: When you play or discard this, draw 3 cards.
flavorText: His skull also draws three cards. Imagine how many cards he could draw with HIS ENTIRE BODY!

name: Harbor Scamp
text: Battlecry: Draw a Pirate.
flavorText: Hey, that gnome looks awfully fishy…

name: Headhunter's Hatchet
text: Battlecry: If you control a Beast, gain +1 Durability.
flavorText: Zul'jin's primary recruiting tool.

name: Headmaster Kel'Thuzad
text: Spellburst: If the spell destroys any minions, summon them.
flavorText: "You wish to know my secrets, hmm? I carry little bits of tuna in the sleeves of my robe, he loves that. Oh, you meant the risen dead? That was trivial, trivial."

name: Heavy Plate
text: Tradeable Gain 8 Armor.
flavorText: "You asked for unbendable, unwavering armor–I don't see why you're upset."

name: Hecklefang Hyena
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to your hero.
flavorText: Even their teeth are laughing at you.

name: Helboar
text: Deathrattle: Give a random Beast in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: Beasts love Helbacon Strips!

name: Hellfire
text: Deal 3 damage to ALL characters.
flavorText: It's spells like these that make it hard for Warlocks to get decent help.

name: Hex
text: Transform a minion into a 0/1 Frog with Taunt.
flavorText: If you Hex a Murloc... it really isn't much of a change, is it?

name: High Abbess Alura
text: Spellburst: Cast a spell from your deck (targets this if possible).
flavorText: She's all about hitting the books. Literally.

name: High Exarch Yrel
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no Neutral cards, gain Rush, Lifesteal, Taunt, and Divine Shield.
flavorText: There can be no neutrality in the fight against darkness.

name: High Inquisitor Whitemane
text: Battlecry: Summon all friendly minions that died this turn.
flavorText: No one told her that champions want to sleep in.

name: Highlord Fordragon
text: Divine Shield After a friendly minion loses Divine Shield, give a minion in your hand +5/+5.
flavorText: "Through my faith and my courage, I shall be protected. And through my honor and sacrifice, another will rise in my place."

name: Hog Rancher
text: Battlecry: Summon a 2/1 Hog with Rush.
flavorText: Suspiciously close to a Quilboar village.

name: Holy Light
text: Restore 8 Health to your hero.
flavorText: If you are often bathed in Holy Light, you should consider wearing sunscreen.

name: Holy Nova
text: Deal 2 damage to all enemy minions. Restore 2 Health to all friendly characters.
flavorText: If the Holy Light forsakes you, good luck casting this spell. Also, you're probably a jerk.

name: Holy Smite
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion.
flavorText: It doesn't matter how pious you are. Everyone needs a good smiting now and again.

name: Horde Operative
text: Battlecry: Copy your opponent's Secrets and put them into play.
flavorText: "We all have our secrets. I mean, your secrets."

name: Horrendous Growth
text: Corrupt: Gain +1/+1. Can be Corrupted endlessly.
flavorText: Stop picking at it! You’re only making it worse.

name: Hot Streak
text: Your next Fire spell this turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: It's easy to catch fire when you're on fire.

name: Hullbreaker
text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Draw a spell. Your hero takes damage equal to its Cost.
flavorText: Breaks through the hard shell to reach the ship's gooey interior.

name: Humongous Razorleaf
text: Can't attack.
flavorText: Loves goblins. In a light cream sauce.

name: Hysteria
text: Choose an enemy minion. It attacks random minions until it dies.
flavorText: "My mount and I share a special connection. Just not a good one."

name: Ice Barrier
text: Secret: When your hero is attacked, gain 8 Armor.
flavorText: This is Rank 1. Rank 2 is Chocolate Milk Barrier.

name: Ice Rager
flavorText: He's a lot cooler than Magma Rager.

name: Idol of Y'Shaarj
text: Summon a 10/10 copy of a minion in your deck.
flavorText: Without a tongue, it speaks in seven. Without a voice, its echo lingers forever.

name: Ignite
text: Deal damage. Shuffle an Ignite into your deck that deals one more damage.
flavorText: "So there I was in the Deadmines, I had VanCleef by the throat, and I was just about to let him have it when... <sniff> What's that smell?"

name: Il'gynoth
text: Lifesteal Your Lifesteal damages the enemy hero instead of healing you.
flavorText: Well, that just sounds like damage with extra steps.

name: Illidari Inquisitor
text: Rush. After your hero attacks an enemy, this attacks it too.
flavorText: Armed with fear, big eyes, ruthless efficiency, almost fanatical devotion to your hero, and nice brown robes.

name: Illidari Studies
text: Discover an Outcast card. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: "Don't read texts and drive."

name: Immolation Aura
text: Deal 1 damage to all minions twice.
flavorText: If you can't take the heat, stop standing in the fire.

name: Imp Swarm (Rank 1)
text: Summon a 3/2 Imp. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: Not a cauldron, or a mischief, or a cackle, but a swarm.

name: Impatient Shopkeep
text: Tradeable Rush
flavorText: "Oi! This ain't a museum, lady."

name: Imported Tarantula
text: Tradeable Deathrattle: Summon two 1/1 Spiders with Poisonous and Rush.
flavorText: Which forbidden forest did you get this from?

name: Imprisoned Antaen
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Can I get a pair of size XXXXXL manacles?

name: Imprisoned Celestial
text: Dormant for 2 turns. Spellburst: Give your minions Divine Shield.
flavorText: "Look at your deck, now back to me, now back at your deck, now back to me. Who am I? None of your—I'm on a horse."

name: Imprisoned Felmaw
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, attack a random enemy.
flavorText: It doesn't care who woke it up, someone's getting bitten.

name: Imprisoned Gan'arg
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, equip a 3/2 Axe.
flavorText: Factory Direct Fiery War Axe. Please allow two turns for delivery.

name: Imprisoned Homunculus
text: Dormant for 2 turns. Taunt
flavorText: He got a time out for excessive vulgarity.

name: Imprisoned Observer
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Currently serving two turns on charges of aggravated minion slaughter.

name: Imprisoned Phoenix
text: Dormant for 2 turns. Spell Damage +2
flavorText: It's actually pretty easy to escape chains when you can burst into flames.

name: Imprisoned Satyr
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, reduce the Cost of a random minion in your hand by (5).
flavorText: "C'mon down to Illhoof's bargain bin! When the satyr's free, he'll lower your fee!"

name: Imprisoned Scrap Imp
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, give all minions in your hand +2/+1.
flavorText: His impish imports imply impressively impetuous impropriety.

name: Imprisoned Sungill
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, summon two 1/1 Murlocs.
flavorText: Imprisoned for ten thousand years! Not because it's a demon. Because of the dancing.

name: Imprisoned Vilefiend
text: Dormant for 2 turns. Rush
flavorText: If you do the time, you gotta make up the time.

name: In Formation!
text: Add 2 random Taunt minions to your hand.
flavorText: None can doubt the strength of the Scholomance student body.

name: Inara Stormcrash
text: On your turn, your hero has +2 Attack and Windfury.
flavorText: A fan favorite, Inara is always met with thunderous applause.

name: Incanter's Flow
text: Reduce the Cost of spells in your deck by (1).
flavorText: "Gettin' them discounts in bulk amounts, spells can come, and spells can go, castin' costs drop with my sweet, sweet flow."

name: Inconspicuous Rider
text: Battlecry: Cast a Secret from your deck.
flavorText: Improvise, adapt, overcome.

name: Infectious Sporeling
text: After this damages a minion, turn it into an Infectious Sporeling.
flavorText: "The best thing about being me—there’s so many 'me's."

name: Infiltrator Lilian
text: Stealth Deathrattle: Summon a 4/2 Forsaken Lilian that attacks a random enemy.
flavorText: She'll get to the bottom of this even if it kills her. Twice!

name: Initiation
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. If that kills it, summon a new copy.
flavorText: The things a murloc's gotta go through to graduate from Scholomance…

name: Injured Blademaster
text: Battlecry: Deal 4 damage to HIMSELF.
flavorText: He claims it is an old war wound, but we think he just cut himself shaving.

name: Injured Marauder
text: Taunt Battlecry: Deal 6 damage to this minion.
flavorText: He’ll keep going despite the neighsayers.

name: Innervate
text: Gain 1 Mana Crystal this turn only.
flavorText: Some druids still have flashbacks from strangers yelling "Innervate me!!" at them.

name: Insatiable Felhound
text: Taunt Corrupt: Gain +1/+1 and Lifesteal.
flavorText: Back-to-back winner of the annual hot dog eating contest... and the judge-eating contest.

name: Insight
text: Draw a minion. Corrupt: Reduce its Cost by (2).
flavorText: Shouldn't the eyes be facing backwards for insight?

name: Instructor Fireheart
text: Battlecry: Discover a spell that costs (1) or more. If you play it this turn, repeat this effect.
flavorText: When you have fire in your heart, even death can't stop you.

name: Intrepid Initiate
text: Spellburst: Gain +2 Attack.
flavorText: How you like them apples?

name: Investment Opportunity
text: Draw an Overload card.
flavorText: "It's a real fixer-upper. I mean a REAL fixer upper."

name: Invigorating Sermon
text: Give +1/+1 to all minions in your hand, deck, and battlefield.
flavorText: Every underdog sports coach knows this one.

name: Irebound Brute
text: Taunt Costs (1) less for each card drawn this turn.
flavorText: "You don't understand… ogres are an untapped market for vengeance and hatred!"

name: Ironbark
text: Give a minion +1/+3 and Taunt. Costs (0) if you have at least 7 Mana Crystals.
flavorText: "The important thing, son, is to protect your spores! I have spoken!"

name: Ironbeak Owl
text: Battlecry: Silence a minion.
flavorText: Their wings are silent but their screech is... whatever the opposite of silent is.

name: Ironclad
text: Battlecry: If your hero has Armor, gain +2/+2.
flavorText: With one inch of clearance, Ironclad proved ineffective against speedbumps.

name: Jace Darkweaver
text: Battlecry: Cast all Fel spells you've played this game (targets enemies if possible).
flavorText: As a former mage, making the transition from fire to felfire was quite easy.

name: Jandice Barov
text: Battlecry: Summon two random 5-Cost minions. Secretly pick one that dies when it takes damage.
flavorText: Her parents own Scholomance. Of course she's going to play tricks on the students!

name: Jerry Rig Carpenter
text: Battlecry: Draw a Choose One spell and split it.
flavorText: Choose Two – Good; Cheap; or Fast.

name: Jewel of N'Zoth
text: Summon three friendly Deathrattle minions that died this game.
flavorText: This coveted gem calls for you to free it… and unleash an inescapable prison.

name: Judgment of Justice
text: Secret: When an enemy minion attacks, set its Attack and Health to 1.
flavorText: Look, we don't need a jury. We've got a paladin right here!

name: Judicious Junior
text: Lifesteal
flavorText: She's judge, jury, and junior!

name: Jungle Panther
text: Stealth
flavorText: Stranglethorn is a beautiful place to visit, but you wouldn't want to live there.

name: K'thir Ritualist
text: Taunt Battlecry: Add a random 4-Cost minion to your opponent's hand.
flavorText: Something evil this way comes… and it's bringing friends over!

name: Kabal Outfitter
text: Battlecry and Deathrattle: Give another random friendly minion +1/+1.
flavorText: Don’t ask her for feathers on your necklace though.

name: Kael'thas Sunstrider
text: Every third spell you cast each turn costs (1).
flavorText: “Descent of Dragons was merely a set back!”

name: Kanrethad Ebonlocke
text: Your Demons cost (1) less. Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Kanrethad Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: After Illidan's downfall, Kanrethad formed the Council of the Black Harvest to study Illidan's fel magic. Some say he was... green with envy.

name: Kargal Battlescar
text: Battlecry: Summon a 5/5 Lookout for each Watch Post you've summoned this game.
flavorText: One if by land, two if by tree.

name: Kargath Bladefist
text: Rush Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Kargath Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: He rules the Shattered Hand orc clan with an iron... bladefist.

name: Kayn Sunfury
text: Charge All friendly attacks ignore Taunt.
flavorText: "Armor and heals may slow my zeal, but fel and glaives excite me!"

name: Kazakus, Golem Shaper
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no 4-Cost cards, build a custom Golem.
flavorText: With a little love and some tenderness, we’ll CRUSH OUR FOES!

name: Keli'dan the Breaker
text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion. If drawn this turn, instead destroy all minions except this one.
flavorText: He calms down a lot if you just give him a turn.

name: Keymaster Alabaster
text: Whenever your opponent draws a card, add a copy to your hand that costs (1).
flavorText: The key to his mastery is a solid stack of backup copies.

name: Keywarden Ivory
text: Battlecry: Discover a Dual Class spell from any class. Spellburst: Get another copy.
flavorText: She learned exactly one thing from her old man: copying.

name: Kindling Elemental
text: Battlecry: The next Elemental you play costs (1) less.
flavorText: Burn baby burn. Little inferno!

name: King Krush
text: Charge
flavorText: The best defense against King Krush is to have someone you don’t like standing in front of you.

name: King Mukla
text: Battlecry: Give your opponent 2 Bananas.
flavorText: King Mukla wanders Jaguero Isle, searching for love.

name: Kiri, Chosen of Elune
text: Battlecry: Add a Solar Eclipse and Lunar Eclipse to your hand.
flavorText: Now, when the Sun is between the Moon and the Azeroth... that's when you've got a problem.

name: Knife Vendor
text: Battlecry: Deal 4 damage to each hero.
flavorText: "They're perfectly safe! These gloves totally aren't hiding any bandages."

name: Knight of Anointment
text: Battlecry: Draw a Holy spell.
flavorText: "I dub thee... injured."

name: Kobold Geomancer
text: Spell Damage +1
flavorText: In the old days, Kobolds were the finest candle merchants in the land. Then they got pushed too far...

name: Kodo Mount
text: Give a minion +4/+2 and Rush. When it dies, summon a Kodo.
flavorText: No matter how big they are or how many times you tell them no, they STILL won't stay off the couch.

name: Kolkar Pack Runner
text: After you cast a spell, summon a 1/1 Hyena with Rush.
flavorText: Is he running or galloping?

name: Kor'vas Bloodthorn
text: Charge, Lifesteal After you play a card with Outcast, return this to your hand.
flavorText: Illidan taught her that demon hunters should sacrifice EVERYTHING… but she still brought Lifesteal just in case.

name: Kresh, Lord of Turtling
text: Frenzy: Gain 8 Armor. Deathrattle: Equip a 2/5 Turtle Spike.
