flavorText: Never should have flushed him.

name: Krolusk Barkstripper
text: Spellburst: Destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: My friend went krolusk tipping once… once!

name: Kul Tiran Chaplain
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion +2 Health.
flavorText: The maritime Kul Tiran clergy are unique among priests for using holy saltwater.

name: Kurtrus Ashfallen
text: Battlecry: Attack the left and right-most enemy minions. Outcast: Immune this turn.
flavorText: Kurtrus fled the Black Temple, abandoning Illidan's cause, to seek revenge against the Dreadlord Anetheron.

name: Lab Partner
text: Spell Damage +1
flavorText: "Professor, a gnome burned my homework!"

name: Lady Anacondra
text: Your Nature spells cost (2) less.
flavorText: Do you think she got her name before or after she turned into a snake?

name: Lady Liadrin
text: Battlecry: Add a copy of each spell you cast on friendly characters this game to your hand.
flavorText: When it comes to spells, she loves 'em then she librams.

name: Lady Prestor
text: Battlecry: Transform minions in your deck into random Dragons. (They keep their original stats and Cost.)
flavorText: To her credit, the best bodyguard for the king WOULD be a dragon in disguise.

name: Lady Vashj
text: Spell Damage +1 Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Vashj Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: Personal handmaiden to Queen Azshara turned lieutenant to Illidan Stormrage. Also quite the hair sssstylist.

name: Lake Thresher
text: Also damages the minions next to whomever this attacks.
flavorText: "There’s a monster in the lake?!" "That’s not a monster, that’s Gary."

name: Lakkari Felhound
text: Taunt Battlecry: Discard your two lowest-Cost cards.
flavorText: Guaranteed to track tar all over your carpet.

name: Landscaping
text: Summon two 2/2 Treants.
flavorText: We'll put a happy tree right here... and give him a little friend.

name: Landslide
text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. If you're Overloaded, deal 1 damage again.
flavorText: "And they win it by a landslide! Wait, where did all the other racers go?"

name: Leatherworking Kit
text: After three friendly Beasts die, draw a Beast and give it +1/+1. Lose 1 Durability.
flavorText: Combining taxidermy and tailoring.

name: Libram of Hope
text: Restore 8 Health. Summon an 8/8 Guardian with Taunt and Divine Shield.
flavorText: "Think you got lethal? Libram of NOPE!"

name: Libram of Judgment
text: Corrupt: Gain Lifesteal.
flavorText: You really can't judge a book by its cover.

name: Libram of Justice
text: Equip a 1/4 weapon. Change the Health of all enemy minions to 1.
flavorText: Proper justice. Throw the book at him!

name: Libram of Wisdom
text: Give a minion +1/+1 and "Deathrattle: Add a 'Libram of Wisdom' spell to your hand."
flavorText: The best wisdom is passed on.

name: Lightbringer's Hammer
text: Lifesteal Can't attack heroes.
flavorText: This entire city must be purged. Or at least just the minions.

name: Lightning Bloom
text: Gain 2 Mana Crystals this turn only. Overload: (2)
flavorText: Curiously, this plant never blooms in the same place twice.

name: Lightning Bolt
text: Deal 3 damage. Overload: (1)
flavorText: Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt!

name: Lightning Storm
text: Deal 3 damage to all enemy minions. Overload: (2)
flavorText: An umbrella won't be effective, I'm afraid.

name: Lightshower Elemental
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Restore 8 Health to all friendly characters.
flavorText: The forecast calls for light showers, but you won’t need an umbrella.

name: Lightspawn
text: This minion's Attack is always equal to its Health.
flavorText: Spawn of the Light? Or Pawn of the Lights?

name: Lightsteed
text: Your healing effects also give affected minions +2 Health.
flavorText: All the steed, half the calories.

name: Lilypad Lurker
text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, transform an enemy minion into a 0/1 Frog with Taunt.
flavorText: Honestly, the frog did nothing wrong.

name: Line Hopper
text: Your Outcast cards cost (1) less.
flavorText: There are two things Demon Hunters know: hopping, and cutting.

name: Lion's Frenzy
text: Has Attack equal to the number of cards you've drawn this turn.
flavorText: Only as sharp as your draw.

name: Lion's Guard
text: Battlecry: If you have 15 or less Health, gain +2/+4 and Taunt.
flavorText: She takes the lion's share of the credit, too.

name: Living Seed (Rank 1)
text: Draw a Beast. Reduce its Cost by (1). (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: Every desert needs an oasis. And it's Guff's duty to make it happen.

name: Loan Shark
text: Battlecry: Give your opponent a Coin. Deathrattle: You get two.
flavorText: Pay up or you'll be swimming with the fishes.

name: Lock and Load
text: Each time you cast a spell this turn, add a random Hunter card to your hand.
flavorText: Rexxar narrowed his eyes, grabbed his machine gun, and said: "It's go time. Lock and load." This card pays homage to that special moment.

name: Lone Champion
text: Battlecry: If you control no other minions, gain Taunt and Divine Shield.
flavorText: He is a champion, with no friends. He'll keep on fighting, til the end!

name: Loot Hoarder
text: Deathrattle: Draw a card.
flavorText: Always roll need.

name: Lord Barov
text: Battlecry: Set the Health of all other minions to 1. Deathrattle: Deal 1 damage to all minions.
flavorText: Alexei Barov stayed at Scholomance despite leasing it to Kel’Thuzad. He says it’s for "supervision."

name: Lord Jaraxxus
text: Battlecry: Equip a 3/8 Blood Fury.
flavorText: "TRIFLING GNOME! YOUR ARROGANCE WILL BE YOUR UNDOING!!!!"

name: Lorekeeper Polkelt
text: Battlecry: Reorder your deck from the highest Cost card to the lowest Cost card.
flavorText: quicksort [] = [] quicksort (x:xs) = quicksort small ++ (x : quicksort large) where small = [y | y <- xs, y <= x] large = [y | y <- xs, y > x]

name: Lost in the Park
text: Questline: Gain 4 Attack with your hero. Reward: Gain 5 Armor.
flavorText: Mister, have you seen my Archdruid?

name: Lothar
text: At the end of your turn, attack a random enemy minion. If it dies, gain +3/+3.
flavorText: Has been around since before there were paladins and those newfangled paladin mechs.

name: Lothraxion the Redeemed
text: Battlecry: For the rest of the game, after you summon a Silver Hand Recruit, give it Divine Shield.
flavorText: So infused with the Light, he has to wear double sleep masks at night.

name: Luckysoul Hoarder
text: Battlecry: Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck. Corrupt: Draw a card.
flavorText: Always brings his own reusable shopping bag, satchel, barrel, trunk, tray, and fluffy pillow.

name: Lunar Eclipse
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Your next spell this turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: When the Azeroth is between the Sun and the Moon.

name: Lushwater Murcenary
text: Battlecry: If you control a Murloc, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: You can't just switch sides because they have more fish!

name: Lushwater Scout
text: After you summon a Murloc, give it +1 Attack and Rush.
flavorText: Only knows how to play "Careless Murgl" and "Mrgl Mrgl Little Star."

name: Mad Bomber
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage randomly split between all other characters.
flavorText: He's not really all that crazy, he is just not as careful with explosives as he should be.

name: Maddest Bomber
text: Battlecry: Deal 12 damage randomly split among all other characters.
flavorText: Talk about a name that limits design space.

name: Maestra of the Masquerade
text: You start the game as a different class until you play a Rogue card.
flavorText: She doesn't drop character until after the DVD commentary.

name: Magehunter
text: Rush Whenever this attacks a minion, Silence it.
flavorText: Hates waiting. Abhors chit chat. Fond of the color purple.

name: Magicfin
text: After a friendly Murloc dies, add a random Legendary minion to your hand.
flavorText: The best part is when he pulls Deathwing out of a top hat!

name: Magtheridon
text: Dormant. Battlecry: Summon three 1/3 enemy Warders. When they die, destroy all minions and awaken.
flavorText: Came from another world to invade Outland and bend it to his will… only to be overthrown by an elf from another world who invaded Outland and bent it to his will.

name: Maiev Shadowsong
text: Battlecry: Choose a minion. It goes Dormant for 2 turns.
flavorText: Go directly to Demon Jail. Do not attack minions, do not collect mana crystals.

name: Mailbox Dancer
text: Battlecry: Add a Coin to your hand. Deathrattle: Give your opponent one.
flavorText: He is the reason why we have 7 mailboxes in this district.

name: Malevolent Strike
text: Destroy a minion. Costs (1) less for each card in your deck that didn't start there.
flavorText: "I don't know how those got in there, but I'm blaming you two."

name: Malygos the Spellweaver
text: Battlecry: Draw spells until your hand is full.
flavorText: After many years, Malygos has decided mortals can use magic. ALL THE MAGIC!

name: Man the Cannons
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion and 1 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: Now THAT’S a lotta splash damage!

name: Man'ari Mosher
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly Demon +3 Attack and Lifesteal this turn.
flavorText: "E.T.C. is sooo mainstream. Have you heard of Blight Boar?"

name: Man-at-Arms
text: Battlecry: If you have a weapon equipped, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: Arch nemesis of the Man-at-Legs.

name: Mana Tide Totem
text: At the end of your turn, draw a card.
flavorText: It is said that some shaman can say "Floatin' totem" 10 times, fast.

name: Manafeeder Panthara
text: Battlecry: If you've used your Hero Power this turn, draw a card.
flavorText: Feeds on mana, crystal kibble, and whatever it was you were just snacking on.

name: Mankrik
text: Battlecry: Help Mankrik find his wife! She was last seen somewhere in your deck.
flavorText: Relives his nightmare every day a new Horde player is created.

name: Mark of the Spikeshell
text: Give a minion +2/+2. If it has Taunt, add a copy of it to your hand.
flavorText: "I'm DEFINITELY turtle-y enough for the turtle club."

name: Mark of the Wild
text: Give a minion Taunt and +2/+3. (+2 Attack/+3 Health)
flavorText: Not to be confused with Jim of the Wild.

name: Marrowslicer
text: Battlecry: Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck.
flavorText: Perfect for killing the first boss in Icecrown Citadel.

name: Marsh Hydra
text: Rush After this attacks, add a random 8-Cost minion to your hand.
flavorText: Three heads of marsh-mashing, bog-bashing, swamp-stomping fury!

name: Marshspawn
text: Battlecry: If you cast a spell last turn, Discover a spell.
flavorText: Hopes to someday promote to Marshsqueen.

name: Mask of C'Thun
text: Deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Hide in the mask, but it will wear you. Through its gleaming eye, you shall see true.

name: Maxima Blastenheimer
text: Battlecry: Summon a minion from your deck. It attacks the enemy hero, then dies.
flavorText: Believe it or not, this is only the faire's fourth most dangerous game.

name: Meeting Stone
text: At the end of your turn, add a 2/2 Adventurer with a random bonus effect to your hand.
flavorText: "I'm clicking on it, but nothing's happening."

name: Menacing Nimbus
text: Battlecry: Add a random Elemental to your hand.
flavorText: Electra stores her elementals in the cloud.

name: Menagerie Warden
text: Battlecry: Choose a friendly Beast. Summon a copy of it.
flavorText: Please? Can I keep him? I promise to clean his cage every day.

name: Metamorfin
text: Taunt Battlecry: If you've cast a Fel spell this turn, gain +2/+2.
flavorText: Always wanted to be the green ranger.

name: Metamorphosis
text: Swap your Hero Power to "Deal 4 damage." After 2 uses, swap it back.
flavorText: As the humble caterpillar becomes a beautiful butterfly, so too does a demon hunter become a hideous mass of writhing destruction and unfettered chaos.

name: Midway Maniac
text: Taunt
flavorText: Faire owners hate him! Learn his secrets with one simple spell!

name: Mindrender Illucia
text: Battlecry: Replace your hand with a copy of your opponent's until end of turn.
flavorText: "…and that's how I ended up with a Murloc Cultural Studies major."

name: Minefield
text: Deal 5 damage randomly split among all minions.
flavorText: Dodge bombs like you're playing Tonksweeper!

name: Mini-Mage
text: Stealth Spell Damage +1
flavorText: He is sometimes found hiding in the treasure chest in the Gurubashi Arena.

name: Mirror Entity
text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, summon a copy of it.
flavorText: "You go first." - Krush'gor the Behemoth, to his pet boar.

name: Mistrunner
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion +3/+3. Overload: (1)
flavorText: "Get IT off me!!!"

name: Mo'arg Artificer
text: All minions take double damage from spells.
flavorText: Double-damage. You know the drill.

name: Mo'arg Forgefiend
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Gain 8 Armor.
flavorText: Enraged not by fel energies, but by an itchy nose he cannot scratch.

name: Mok'Nathal Lion
text: Rush. Battlecry: Choose a friendly minion. Gain a copy of its Deathrattle.
flavorText: Never underestimate a lioness when her pride is on the line.

name: Molten Blast
text: Deal 2 damage. Summon that many 1/1 Elementals.
flavorText: Well, how would YOU celebrate after finals week?!

name: Monstrous Parrot
text: Battlecry: Repeat the last friendly Deathrattle that triggered.
flavorText: What kind of crackers are you feeding that thing?

name: Moonfang
text: Can only take 1 damage at a time.
flavorText: Moonforehead just didn't have the same ring to it.

name: Moonlit Guidance
text: Discover a copy of a card in your deck. If you play it this turn, draw the original.
flavorText: Guff always makes the best decisions after 2 AM.

name: Moontouched Amulet
text: Give your hero +4 Attack this turn. Corrupt: And gain 6 Armor.
flavorText: The Suntouched Amulet melted.

name: Mor'shan Elite
text: Taunt. Battlecry: If your hero attacked this turn, summon a copy of this.
flavorText: "Fear not the orc who has slain a million training dummies, but the orc who keeps CAMPING MY CORPSE!"

name: Mor'shan Watch Post
text: Can't attack. After your opponent plays a minion, summon a 2/2 Grunt.
flavorText: Pushing into Ashenvale made this post uneventful.

name: Mordresh Fire Eye
text: Battlecry: If you've dealt 10 damage with your Hero Power this game, deal 10 damage to all enemies. ( left!) (Ready!)
flavorText: You're not hardcore unless you died hardcore.

name: Mortal Coil
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If that kills it, draw a card.
flavorText: If your spells look like horrifying skulls, let's be honest, you should get to draw some cards.

name: Mozaki, Master Duelist
text: After you cast a spell, gain Spell Damage +1.
flavorText: Treats her students like her peers, which means defeating them in one-sided duels all day long.

name: Mr. Smite
text: Your Pirates have Charge.
flavorText: “Please, Mr. Smite was my father. Call me Yorik.”

name: Multicaster
text: Battlecry: Draw a card for each different spell school you've cast this game.
flavorText: Has a questionable talent tree.

name: Murgur Murgurgle
text: Divine Shield Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Murgurgle Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: Murlocs are not native to Outland. When the Sungills arrived, one among them rose to the challenge of this dark world. They call him... Murgurgle. Murgur Murgurgle.

name: Murloc Tidecaller
text: Whenever you summon a Murloc, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: This guy gets crazy strong at family reunions.

name: Murloc Tidehunter
text: Battlecry: Summon a 1/1 Murloc Scout.
flavorText: "Death will rise, from the tides!"

name: Murloc Tinyfin
flavorText: High mortality rate, from often being hugged to death.

name: Mutanus the Devourer
text: Battlecry: Eat a minion in your opponent's hand. Gain its stats.
flavorText: As long as Naralex stays under the blanket, Mutanus can't get him.

name: Mystery Winner
text: Battlecry: Discover a Secret.
flavorText: Yeah, but the mystery prize could be anything! Even a boat!

name: N'Zoth, God of the Deep
text: Battlecry: Resurrect a friendly minion of each minion type.
flavorText: It really just wants to cuddle all the creatures of Azeroth.

name: Nagrand Slam
text: Summon four 3/5 Clefthoofs that attack random enemies.
flavorText: Come on and slam, and welcome to Nagrand!

name: Natalie Seline
text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion and gain its Health.
flavorText: She discovered Xal'atath, Blade of the Black Empire, a terrible weapon of shadow magic that could both swallow a soul and cut a mean julienne.

name: Nature Studies
text: Discover a spell. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: "I have a first edition! Go ahead, count the rings."

name: Nazmani Bloodweaver
text: After you cast a spell, reduce the cost of a random card in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Her first stage name, Ketchupweaver, failed to excite the audience.

name: Need for Greed
text: Tradeable Draw 3 cards. If drawn this turn, this costs (3).
flavorText: Sorry guys, I TOTALLY meant to click greed.

name: Neeru Fireblade
text: Battlecry: If your deck is empty, open a portal that fills your board with 3/2 Imps each turn.
flavorText: Look at this guy! He’s obviously evil! OBVIOUSLY!!!

name: Nerubian Egg
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 4/4 Nerubian.
flavorText: Eggs are a good source of protein and Nerubians.

name: Netherwalker
text: Battlecry: Discover a Demon.
flavorText: You got to Nethercrawl before you can Netherwalk.

name: Netherwind Portal
text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, summon a random 4-Cost minion.
flavorText: More aromatic than a regular portal.

name: Nightshade Matron
text: Rush Battlecry: Discard your highest Cost card.
flavorText: Throws shade at those "high-cost" minions.

name: Nitroboost Poison
text: Give a minion +2 Attack. Corrupt: And your weapon.
flavorText: Pouring iced milk into your vehicle's fuel tank does NOT provide a Nitro boost, but it does go great with your victory cookies.

name: Noble Mount
text: G ive a minion +1/+1 and Divine Shield. When it dies, summon a Warhorse.
flavorText: The Horde rued the day that Cariel was allowed to take her pet to work.

name: Noble Sacrifice
text: Secret: When an enemy attacks, summon a 2/1 Defender as the new target.
flavorText: We will always remember you, "Defender!"

name: Nobleman
text: Battlecry: Create a Golden copy of a random card in your hand.
flavorText: What class are you? 'Upper.'

name: Nofin Can Stop Us
text: Give your minions +1/+1. Give your Murlocs an extra +1/+1.
flavorText: "I'm having a good time! I don't want to stop at all!"

name: Nordrassil Druid
text: Battlecry: The next spell you cast this turn costs (3) less.
flavorText: The World Tree Nordrassil provides life-giving energy to the world--and excellent mana savings.

name: Northshire Farmer
text: Battlecry: Choose a friendly Beast. Shuffle three 3/3 copies into your deck.
flavorText: Dual-classed into Farmer/Rancher.

name: Northwatch Commander
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, draw a minion.
flavorText: It was all going well until some Horde had the cunning idea of attacking from the south.

name: Nourish
text: Choose One - Gain 2 Mana Crystals; or Draw 3 cards.
flavorText: Druids take nourishment from many things: the power of nature, the songbird's chirp, a chocolate cake.

name: Novice Zapper
text: Spell Damage +1 Overload: (1)
flavorText: The novices would prefer that he did not.

name: Nozdormu the Eternal
text: Start of Game: If this is in BOTH players' decks, turns are only 15 seconds long.
flavorText: Live life in the fast lane. As long as your opponent does too.

name: Oasis Ally
text: Secret: When a friendly minion is attacked, summon a 3/6 Water Elemental.
flavorText: As gentle as a bellyflop.

name: Oasis Thrasher
text: Frenzy: Deal 3 damage to the enemy Hero.
flavorText: Didn't get tickets for E.T.C.'s show.

name: Occult Conjurer
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, summon a copy of this.
flavorText: Like mirror image, but more secretive and angsty.

name: Ogremancer
text: Whenever your opponent casts a spell, summon a 2/2 Skeleton with Taunt.
flavorText: After their third attempt, Tharg began to suspect that Krul was summoning the skeletons on purpose.

name: Oh My Yogg!
text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, they instead cast a random one of the same Cost.
flavorText: Many wonders lie within, but they are not mere toys when your mind is their plaything.

name: Oil Rig Ambusher
text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage. If this entered your hand this turn, deal 4 instead.
flavorText: Days since last accident: 0

name: Onyx Magescribe
text: Spellburst: Add 2 random spells from your class to your hand.
flavorText: Sometimes you gotta spend spells to earn spells.

name: Onyxia the Broodmother
text: At the end of each turn, fill your board with 1/1 Whelps.
flavorText: Throw more dots, throw more dots, more dots, more dots!

name: Open the Cages
text: Secret: When your turn starts, if you control two minions, summon an Animal Companion.
flavorText: "Coming out of my cage, and I'm dead by turn nine..."

name: Optimistic Ogre
text: 50% chance to attack the correct enemy.
flavorText: "What if this goes wrong?" "But what if this goes right?"

name: Oracle of Elune
text: After you play a minion that costs (2) or less, summon a copy of it.
flavorText: Even the moon goddess needs to back up her databases.

name: Outrider's Axe
text: After your hero attacks and kills a minion, draw a card.
flavorText: "I only have to get 4 Zhevra hooves? How hard could that be?"

name: Overconfident Orc
text: Taunt While at full Health, this has +2 Attack.
flavorText: "I am da powerful! You are da poop!"

name: Overdraft
text: Tradeable Unlock your Overloaded Mana Crystals to deal that much damage.
flavorText: Wait. It costs mana to be out of mana?!

name: Overgrowth
text: Gain two empty Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Zangarmarsh: it's a fungal out there!

name: Overlord Runthak
text: Rush. Whenever this attacks, give +1/+1 to all minions in your hand.
flavorText: Knows how to lift everyone up while tearing every enemy down.

name: Overlord Saurfang
text: Battlecry: Resurrect 2 friendly Frenzy minions. Deal 1 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: Eats more than his fair share of sour candy.

name: Overwhelm
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. Deal one more damage for each Beast you control.
flavorText: Scholomance student Brewfest prank gone terribly, terribly awry.

name: Pack Kodo
text: Battlecry: Discover a Beast, Secret, or weapon.
flavorText: He looks simple, but there’s a lot to unpack.

name: Pack Tactics
text: Secret: When a friendly minion is attacked, summon a 3/3 copy.
flavorText: "Just you wait, I’ll go get on my main!"

name: Package Runner
text: Can only attack if you have at least 8 cards in hand.
flavorText: He could go... all... the... way!

name: Palm Reading
text: Discover a spell. Reduce the Cost of spells in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Actual palms not required.

name: Pandaren Importer
text: Battlecry: Discover a spell that didn't start in your deck.
flavorText: She carries everything you didn't want and more!

name: Parade Leader
text: After you summon a Rush minion, give it +2 Attack.
flavorText: He's always going to reign on his parade.

name: Paralytic Poison
text: Give your weapon +1 Attack and "Your hero is Immune while attacking."
flavorText: The hammer is overkill.

name: Park Panther
text: Rush. Whenever this attacks, give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Somebody called animal control once. It didn't work out very well for anybody.

name: Parrrley
text: Swap this for a card in your opponent's deck.
flavorText: Time to engage in some unfriendly negotiations.

name: Partner Assignment
text: Add a random 2-Cost and 3-Cost Beast to your hand.
flavorText: In every group assignment, someone does all the legwork.

name: Party Up!
text: Summon five 2/2 Adventurers with random bonus effects.
flavorText: Random? But what if we don't get a tank?

name: Patient Assassin
text: Stealth Poisonous
flavorText: He’s not really that patient. It just takes a while for someone to walk by that he can actually reach.

name: Peasant
text: At the start of your turn, draw a card.
flavorText: Better pay them, or they'll join the Defias.

name: Pen Flinger
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion. Spellburst: Return this to your hand.
flavorText: The pen is also a more aerodynamic short-range projectile than the sword.

name: Peon
text: Frenzy: Add a random spell from your class to your hand.
flavorText: Joke's on the peon: the job's never done.

name: Perpetual Flame
text: Deal 3 damage to a random enemy minion. If it dies, recast this. Overload: (1)
flavorText: Flame is perpetual.* *Perpetual only applies to current turn.

name: Persistent Peddler
text: Tradeable Deathrattle: Summon a Persistent Peddler from your deck.
flavorText: Loves pyramid schemes and bike rides.

name: Petting Zoo
text: Summon a 3/3 Strider. Repeat for each Secret you control.
flavorText: Welcome to the petting zoo. DO NOT TOUCH THE ANIMALS.

name: Piercing Shot
text: Deal 6 damage to a minion. Excess damage hits the enemy hero.
flavorText: Goblins hate wasting money on unnecessary ammunition.

name: Pit Commander
text: Taunt At the end of your turn, summon a Demon from your deck.
flavorText: "Pit! Do as I say!"

name: Pit Master
text: Battlecry: Summon a 3/2 Duelist. Corrupt: Summon two.
flavorText: If you win your duel, he'll throw in some of his famous Pit Master barbecue.

name: Plagiarize
text: Secret: At the end of your opponent's turn, add copies of the cards they played to your hand.
flavorText: Copying is just using your resources wisely.

name: Plague Scientist
text: Combo: Give a friendly minion Poisonous.
flavorText: The excruciating pain means it's working!

name: Plagued Protodrake
text: Deathrattle: Summon a random 7-Cost minion.
flavorText: "What’s in the drake?! WHAT’S IN THE DRAKE?"

name: Plaguemaw the Rotting
text: After a friendly minion with Taunt dies, summon a new copy of it without Taunt.
flavorText: This is why you should brush your teeth three times a day!

name: Playmaker
text: After you play a Rush minion, summon a copy with 1 Health remaining.
flavorText: "Here's the plan: you go left, I go right, and the wounded guy takes the hit."

name: Possessed Villager
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Shadowbeast.
flavorText: It's like a pinata! A lame disgusting horrific pinata.

name: Potion of Illusion
text: Add 1/1 copies of your minions to your hand. They cost (1).
flavorText: Unfortunately, there's no potion that can make you unsee all the faces in that bottle.

name: Pounce
text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Comes with an overwhelming urge to jump into the nearest open box.

name: Power Infusion
text: Give a minion +2/+6.
flavorText: It infuses, it enthuses, it amuses!

name: Power Word: Feast
text: Give a minion +2/+2. Restore it to full Health at the end of this turn.
flavorText: Some people are here for the stellar, world-renowned academic program. Others are here for the buffet.

name: Power Word: Fortitude
text: Give a minion +3/+5. Costs (1) less for each spell in your hand.
flavorText: Part of a balanced breakfast.

name: Power of the Wild
text: Choose One - Give your minions +1/+1; or Summon a 3/2 Panther.
flavorText: Never look a panther in the eye. Or is it 'Always look a panther in the eye'? Well, it's one of those.

name: Preparation
text: The next spell you cast this turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: "Be Prepared" - Rogue Motto

name: Prestor's Pyromancer
text: Battlecry: Your next Fire spell has Spell Damage +2.
flavorText: Ah, yeah. This guy. Definitely not an evil dragon in disguise either.

name: Pride's Fury
text: Give your minions +1/+3.
flavorText: Day 4: I think they're starting to suspect.

name: Priest of An'she
text: Taunt. Battlecry: If you've restored Health this turn, gain +3/+3.
flavorText: "An’she?" "Bless you!" "No, you, An'she…" "Bless you again!"

name: Priestess of Fury
text: At the end of your turn, deal 6 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Furious that she only has six warglaives. The Sightless Watcher has eight! The fel is always greener on the other side.

name: Primal Dungeoneer
text: Battlecry: Draw a spell. If it's a Nature spell, also draw an Elemental.
flavorText: They wanted a Mature Dungeoneer. Instead they got this.

name: Primordial Protector
text: Battlecry: Draw your highest Cost spell. Summon a random minion with the same Cost.
flavorText: I thought the "shape of water" meant something else.

name: Primordial Studies
text: Discover a Spell Damage minion. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: A long forgotten tome whose very essence seeps of magic. 40 dust, used.

name: Prismatic Jewel Kit
text: After a friendly minion loses Divine Shield, give minions in your hand +1/+1. Lose 1 Durability.
flavorText: The divine trick to jewelcrafting is tumbling your own rocks.

name: Prize Plunderer
text: Combo: Deal 1 damage to a minion for each other card you've played this turn.
flavorText: But he'll never be able to plunder the prize of a happy childhood.

name: Prize Vendor
text: Battlecry: Each player draws a card.
flavorText: He's just making sure they're real. Authentic tickets taste like strawberry.

name: Professor Slate
text: Your spells are Poisonous.
flavorText: "Don’t worry, this will be over in a second. It might FEEL like an eternity, but I assure you, it’s quite quick!"

name: Prospector's Caravan
text: At the start of your turn, give all minions in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: Prospectors came from all around in the Golden Legendary Rush of '49.

name: Proving Grounds
text: Summon two minions from your deck. They fight!
flavorText: 1v1 me on Proving Grounds, DH only, no items, 4 stocks.

name: Provoke
text: Tradeable Choose a friendly minion. Enemy minions attack it.
flavorText: "Heh, Greetings. Heh, Greetings. Heh, Greetings. I will crush you!"

name: Psyche Split
text: Give a minion +1/+2. Summon a copy of it.
flavorText: This is how the arakkoa make friends.

name: Psychic Conjurer
text: Battlecry: Copy a card in your opponent’s deck and add it to your hand.
flavorText: "I see... a WISP? Why do you have a wisp?!"

name: Psyfiend
text: After you cast a Shadow spell, deal 2 damage to each hero.
flavorText: Listens to a LOT of K-pop.

name: Pursuit of Justice
text: Give +1 Attack to Silver Hand Recruits you summon this game.
flavorText: "Is this about justice or just us?"

name: Quick Shot
text: Deal 3 damage. If your hand is empty, draw a card.
flavorText: Han shot first.

name: Raging Felscreamer
text: Battlecry: The next Demon you play costs (2) less.
flavorText: Screaming loudly will not reduce the cost of non-demonic goods.

name: Raid Leader
text: Your other minions have +1 Attack.
flavorText: "That's a 50 DKP minus!"

name: Raid the Docks
text: Questline: Play 3 Pirates. Reward: Draw a weapon.
flavorText: Winning the annual Ratchet Regatta really went to their heads.

name: Raise Dead
text: Deal 3 damage to your hero. Return two friendly minions that died this game to your hand.
flavorText: Technically, it’s just really late healing.

name: Rally!
text: Resurrect a friendly 1-Cost, 2-Cost, and 3-Cost minion.
flavorText: One for the squire, two for the gnome, three for the glory, and GO, GO, GO!

name: Ramming Mount
text: Give a minion +2/+2 and Immune while attacking. When it dies, summon a Ram.
flavorText: Tavish has some road rage issues to work through.

name: Rancor
text: Deal 2 damage to all minions. Gain 2 Armor for each destroyed.
flavorText: Wise men say "Only fools rush in." Wise Orcs say the opposite.

name: Ras Frostwhisper
text: At the end of your turn, deal 1 damage to all enemies (improved by Spell Damage).
flavorText: Always the favorite of Headmaster Kel'Thuzad, Ras nonetheless received a chilly reception from the other faculty.

name: Ratchet Privateer
text: Battlecry: Give your weapon +1 Attack.
flavorText: There's a fine line between privateering and pirating. It comes down to tax breaks.

name: Rats of Extraordinary Size
text: Summon seven 1/1 Rats. Any that can't fit on the battlefield go to your hand with +4/+4.
flavorText: They don't care if you believe they exist.

name: Rattlegore
text: Deathrattle: Resummon this with -1/-1.
flavorText: He looks bad now, but he was pretty handsome in his 20/20s.

name: Razorboar
text: Deathrattle: Summon a Deathrattle minion that costs (3) or less from your hand.
flavorText: And this little pig built his house out of VENGEANCE.

name: Razorfen Beastmaster
text: Deathrattle: Summon a Deathrattle minion that costs (4) or less from your hand.
flavorText: It's a homebrew variant on my favorite role-playing game.

name: Razormane Battleguard
text: The first Taunt minion you play each turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: Where there's a quill, there's a way.

name: Razormane Raider
text: Frenzy: Attack a random enemy.
flavorText: "Call me hedgehog one more time. I dare you."

name: Reaper's Scythe
text: Spellburst: Also damages adjacent minions this turn.
flavorText: Die. Die. Die.

name: Reckless Apprentice
text: Battlecry: Fire your Hero Power at all enemies.
flavorText: It’s all a great learning experience until someone accidentally aggros the boss.

name: Reckoning
text: Secret: After an enemy minion deals 3 or more damage, destroy it.
flavorText: He would henceforth be known as "Karmerr, the Doom of Kazzak."

name: Redeemed Pariah
text: After you play an Outcast card, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: "Look at this stick. Look at it!"

name: Redgill Razorjaw
text: Rush
flavorText: One fish, two fish, red fish replaces blue fish.

name: Redscale Dragontamer
text: Deathrattle: Draw a Dragon.
flavorText: Sir Finley made this look a lot easier three expansions ago...

name: Refreshing Spring Water
text: Draw 2 cards. Refresh 2 Mana Crystals for each spell drawn.
flavorText: "Mana" is just another name for "electrolytes."

name: Relentless Pursuit
text: Give your hero +4 Attack and Immune this turn.
flavorText: If you steal a Demon Hunter's corn dog, you'll get what's coming.

name: Reliquary of Souls
text: Lifesteal Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Reliquary Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: These three represent Anger, Desire, and Suffering. Much like raid night guild chat.

name: Remote-Controlled Golem
text: After this takes damage, shuffle two Golem Parts into your deck. When drawn, summon a 2/1 Mech.
flavorText: Someone got a little too excited inventing a can opener.

name: Renew
text: Restore 3 Health. Discover a spell.
flavorText: I am rejuvenated, I am renewed, I am my own nightlight!

name: Renowned Performer
text: Rush Deathrattle: Summon two 1/1 Assistants with Taunt.
flavorText: Cutting the assistant in half is the easy part.

name: Replicat-o-tron
text: At the end of your turn, transform a neighbor into a copy of this.
flavorText: According to the Boom Labs sales brochure, it "impractically makes itself!"

name: Resizing Pouch
text: Discover a card with Cost equal to your remaining Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Just don't put a Resizing Pouch inside the Resizing Pouch.

name: Revenant Rascal
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Mana Crystal for each player.
flavorText: Turns out his face really did get stuck that way.

name: Revolve
text: Transform all minions into random ones with the same Cost.
flavorText: "Please don't ride the carousel for thirty minutes after eating. After the carousel eats, I mean."

name: Rigged Faire Game
text: Secret: If you didn't take any damage during your opponent's turn, draw 3 cards.
flavorText: What's faire is fair.

name: Righteous Defense
text: Set a minion's Attack and Health to 1. Give the stats it lost to a minion in your hand.
flavorText: Paladins... Always stealing someone else’s thunder. And stats.

name: Righteous Protector
text: Taunt Divine Shield
flavorText: Original name was Tubular Protector, but this seems more bodacious.

name: Rimetongue
text: After you cast a Frost spell, summon a 1/1 Elemental that Freezes.
flavorText: Warriors are red, Frost spells are blue, If you're being hit by a weapon, Rimetongue's got you.

name: Ring Matron
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon two 3/2 Imps.
flavorText: But where does she keep them?

name: Ring Toss
text: Discover a Secret and cast it. Corrupt: Discover 2 instead.
flavorText: If you liked it, then you shoulda put a ring on it!

name: Ringmaster Whatley
text: Battlecry: Draw a Mech, Dragon, and Pirate.
flavorText: His main qualification is that he'll work with anyone. Or anything.

name: Ringmaster's Baton
text: After your hero attacks, give a Mech, Dragon, and Pirate in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: A mech, a dragon, and a pirate walk into an Old God's gaping maw. The mech was too crunchy, the dragon was too hot, but the pirate was just right.

name: Rinling's Rifle
text: After your hero attacks, Discover a Secret and cast it.
flavorText: This rifle needs a muzzle for its muzzle.

name: Rise to the Occasion
text: Questline: Play 3 different 1-Cost cards. Reward: Equip a 1/4 Light's Justice.
flavorText: Faith is never lost, only repurposed.

name: Ritual of Doom
text: Destroy a friendly minion. If you had 5 or more, summon a 5/5 Demon.
flavorText: "Who wants to sing the Doom song?!"

name: River Crocolisk
flavorText: Edward "Lefty" Smith tried to make luggage out of a river crocolisk once.

name: Robes of Protection
text: Your minions have "Can't be targeted by spells or Hero Powers."
flavorText: Warning: Robes of Protection are intended for targeted effects only and are not an effective defense against Flamestrike, Twisting Nether, or other AOE attacks.

name: Rock Rager
text: Taunt
flavorText: Still doesn't understand why he can't beat Paper Rager.

name: Rockbiter Weapon
text: Give a friendly character +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: This would be real handy if your enemy is made of rock.

name: Rocket Augmerchant
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Rush.
flavorText: "Don't worry, this won't hurt me a bit."

name: Rodent Nest
text: Deathrattle: Summon five 1/1 Rats.
flavorText: Pig sty? No, this is a rat's nest.

name: Rokara
text: Rush After a friendly minion attacks and survives, give it +1/+1.
flavorText: "Tread carefully, but stand tall, and stand together. For strength and honor!" —Rokara

name: Royal Librarian
text: Tradeable Battlecry: Silence a minion.
flavorText: Books on how to flip the Auction House are down that way.

name: Runaway Blackwing
text: At the end of your turn, deal 9 damage to a random enemy minion.
flavorText: It has been 5 minutes since our last Azeroth Racing League violation.

name: Rune Dagger
text: After your hero attacks, gain Spell Damage +1 this turn.
flavorText: Turns out being stabbed makes you more vulnerable to magic.

name: Runed Mithril Rod
text: After you draw 4 cards, reduce the Cost of cards in your hand by (1). Lose 1 Durability.
flavorText: "Please, I need these greens to disenchant them." —Every Enchanter Ever

name: Runed Orb
text: Deal 2 damage. Discover a spell.
flavorText: The most dangerous Winter Veil ornament.

name: Runic Carvings
text: Choose One - Summon four 2/2 Treant Totems; or Overload: (2) to summon them with Rush.
flavorText: "That totem was beautiful… and you runed it!"

name: Rustrot Viper
text: Tradeable Battlecry: Destroy your opponent's weapon.
flavorText: Poisonous to weapons.

name: Ruststeed Raider
text: Taunt, Rush Battlecry: Gain +4 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Three-time winner (and sole survivor) of the Crashes of Outland motocross!

name: Rustsworn Cultist
text: Battlecry: Give your other minions "Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Demon."
flavorText: "Rust… I love it. It's all coarse, and rough, and irritating. And it gets everywhere."

name: Rustsworn Initiate
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Impcaster with Spell Damage +1.
flavorText: The Rusted Legion's training leaves a little to be desired. He hasn't even had a tetanus shot yet!

name: SI:7 Agent
text: Combo: Deal 2 damage.
flavorText: The agents of SI:7 are responsible for Stormwind's covert activities. Their duties include espionage, assassination, and throwing surprise birthday parties for the royal family.

name: SI:7 Assassin
text: Costs (1) less for each SI:7 card you've played this game. Combo: Destroy an enemy minion.
flavorText: You can't keep the streets clean if you're afraid to get your hands dirty.

name: SI:7 Extortion
text: Tradeable Deal 3 damage to an undamaged character.
flavorText: "It's a dangerous world out there. It'd be a shame if your protection insurance were to suddenly run out…"

name: SI:7 Infiltrator
text: Battlecry: Destroy a random enemy Secret.
flavorText: What will she destroy? It’s a secret!

name: SI:7 Informant
text: Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each SI:7 card you've played this game.
flavorText: Sitting in a tavern all day and looking scary is hard work, but somebody has to do it.

name: SI:7 Operative
text: Rush After this attacks a minion, gain Stealth.
flavorText: What do you mean you're out of ponies?

name: SI:7 Skulker
text: Stealth Battlecry: The next card you draw costs (1) less.
flavorText: Burying bones and calling it skullduggery.

name: Saddlemaster
text: After you play a Beast, add a random Beast to your hand.
flavorText: Seat covers. Check. Racing stripes. Check. Cupholder. Check.

name: Safety Inspector
text: Battlecry: Shuffle the lowest-Cost card from your hand into your deck. Draw a card.
flavorText: "All right, you're good. No sign of safety anywhere."

name: Sanctum Chandler
text: After you cast a Fire spell, draw a spell.
flavorText: Has been burning at both ends to keep the place illuminated.

name: Savannah Highmane
text: Deathrattle: Summon two 2/2 Hyenas.
flavorText: In the jungle, the mighty jungle, the lion gets slowly consumed by hyenas.

name: Savory Deviate Delight
text: Transform a minion in both players' hands into a Pirate or Stealth minion.
flavorText: "Savory" is a creative way to put it.

name: Sayge, Seer of Darkmoon
text: Battlecry: Draw (card, cards). (Upgraded for each friendly Secret that has triggered this game!)
flavorText: There are no secrets between us... or refunds.

name: Scabbs Cutterbutter
text: Combo: The next two cards you play this turn cost (3) less.
flavorText: "Never lie, steal, cheat, or drink. Unless you're compelled to, that is…" —Scabbs Cutterbutter

name: Scavenger's Ingenuity
text: Draw a Beast. Give it +2/+2.
flavorText: "A beast, barely alive. Gentlemen, we can rebuild it! Make it stronger, faster... spikier."

name: Scavenging Hyena
text: Whenever a friendly Beast dies, gain +2/+1.
flavorText: Hyenas prefer the bones of kodos or windserpents, but they'll eat pretty much anything. Even Brussels sprouts.

name: Scavenging Shivarra
text: Battlecry: Deal 6 damage randomly split among all other minions.
flavorText: Say what you want but finding a matching set of six swords takes commitment.

name: School Spirits
text: Deal 2 damage to all minions. Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck.
flavorText: "B-E A-G-G-R-E-S-S-I-V-E!"

name: Scrap Golem
text: Taunt. Deathrattle: Gain Armor equal to this minion's Attack.
flavorText: Abuse, reuse, recycle.

name: Scrap Shot
text: Deal 3 damage. Give a random Beast in your hand +3/+3.
flavorText: Make your foe's armor your fauna's fashion!

name: Scrapyard Colossus
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon a 7/7 Felcracked Colossus with Taunt.
flavorText: Heap on heapin' on.

name: Secret Passage
text: Replace your hand with 4 cards from your deck. Swap back next turn.
flavorText: I use this to sneak out at night and do some villainous baking in the kitchen.

name: Seedcloud Buckler
text: Deathrattle: Give your minions Divine Shield.
flavorText: A shield to some, a frisbee to others (mainly dogs).

name: Seek Guidance
text: Questline: Play a 2, 3, and 4-Cost card. Reward: Discover a card from your deck.
flavorText: Xyrella was looking for spiritual guidance but found deck-building tips instead.

name: Selective Breeder
text: Battlecry: Discover a copy of a Beast in your deck.
flavorText: His ethics are top notch. Just look at that smiling kitty!

name: Self-Sharpening Sword
text: After your hero attacks, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: You no longer have to bring a stack of 2 swords to a test!

name: Selfless Sidekick
text: Battlecry: Equip a random weapon from your deck.
flavorText: "I got a real sense of humility from her when she bashed that quilboar's head in."

name: Sen'jin Shieldmasta
text: Taunt
flavorText: Sen'jin Village is nice, if you like trolls and dust.

name: Serena Bloodfeather
text: Battlecry: Choose an enemy minion. Steal Attack and Health from it until this has more.
flavorText: She’s really into networking! After all, she’s introduced countless low-level Horde players to the Spirit Healer.

name: Serpentbloom
text: Give a friendly Beast Poisonous.
flavorText: "Awww, it's so cute!" —Famous last words

name: Serpentshrine Portal
text: Deal 3 damage. Summon a random 3-Cost minion. Overload: (1)
flavorText: This is why you never flush a three-cost minion.

name: Sethekk Veilweaver
text: After you cast a spell on a minion, add a Priest spell to your hand.
flavorText: The Sethekk weren't able to survive this long by being wasteful with their power. Or their wacky hats.

name: Shadow Clone
text: Secret: After a minion attacks your hero, summon a copy of it with Stealth.
flavorText: "You thought you were attacking face, but it was me! You!"

name: Shadow Council
text: Replace your hand with random Demons. Give them +2/+2.
flavorText: Why is everybody in Outland replacing their hands?!

name: Shadow Hunter Vol'jin
text: Battlecry: Choose a minion. Swap it with a random one in its owner's hand.
flavorText: You wouldn’t see this swap-meet on the Zandalari Roadshow.

name: Shadow Word: Death
text: Destroy a minion with 5 or more Attack.
flavorText: If you miss, it leaves a lightning-bolt-shaped scar on your target.

name: Shadow Word: Ruin
text: Destroy all minions with 5 or more Attack.
flavorText: Discovered by a worgen priest after a giant spilled a drink on her new white robes.

name: Shadowblade Slinger
text: Battlecry: If you've taken damage this turn, deal that much to an enemy minion.
flavorText: Throwing knives isn’t easy for a warlock. It’s quite painful, in fact.

name: Shadowcloth Needle
text: After you cast a Shadow spell, deal 1 damage to all enemies. Lose 1 Durability.
flavorText: Makes light of the darkest repair jobs.

name: Shadowed Spirit
text: Deathrattle: Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: They can't all be grim grinning ghosts.

name: Shadowform
text: Your Hero Power becomes 'Deal 2 damage.'
flavorText: If a bright light shines on a priest in Shadowform… do they cast a shadow?

name: Shadowjeweler Hanar
text: After you play a Secret, Discover a Secret from a different class.
flavorText: What is a shadowjeweler? A miserable little pile of secrets.

name: Shadowlight Scholar
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Soul Fragment in your deck to deal 3 damage.
flavorText: Imagine having the power of soul magic and using it as a reading light.

name: Shadowstep
text: Return a friendly minion to your hand. It costs (2) less.
flavorText: Rogue dance troops will sometimes Shadowstep away at the end of a performance. Crowds love it.

name: Shady Bartender
text: Tradeable Battlecry: Give your Demons +2/+2.
flavorText: One sin and tonic, coming right up.

name: Shan'do Wildclaw
text: Choose One - Give Beasts in your deck +1/+1; or Transform into a copy of a friendly Beast.
flavorText: She holds both an academic post and a scratching post.

name: Shard of the Naaru
text: Tradeable Silence all enemy minions.
flavorText: Fell from the sky, huh? I'll give you ten gold.

name: Shardshatter Mystic
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Soul Fragment in your deck to deal 3 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: Enjoys a good soul-crushing defeat.

name: Shattered Rumbler
text: Battlecry: If you cast a spell last turn, deal 2 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO THE GROUND!

name: Shattering Blast
text: Destroy all Frozen minions.
flavorText: Let's be honest, they weren't going to unfreeze anyway.

name: Sheldras Moontree
text: Battlecry: The next 3 spells you draw are Cast When Drawn.
flavorText: Sheldras really went to the park for his pilgrimage.

name: Shenanigans
text: Secret: When your opponent draws their second card in a turn, transform it into a Banana.
flavorText: It's not personal, it's just monkey business.

name: Shield Slam
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion for each Armor you have.
flavorText: "What is a better weapon? The sharp one your enemies expect, or the blunt one they ignore?" - The Art of Warrior, Chapter 9

name: Shield of Honor
text: Give a damaged minion +3 Attack and Divine Shield.
flavorText: "Sir, this shield would've been more helpful last turn!"

name: Shieldmaiden
text: Battlecry: Gain 5 Armor.
flavorText: She has three shieldbearers in her party to supply her with back ups when she gets low on durability.

name: Shifty Sophomore
text: Stealth Spellburst: Add a Combo card to your hand.
flavorText: Experienced enough to do crimes, inexperienced enough to be super obvious about it.

name: Shiver Their Timbers!
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If you control a Pirate, deal 5 instead.
flavorText: Who knew there was overlap between pirates and lumberjacks?

name: Shooting Star
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and the minions next to it.
flavorText: Literally starstruck.

name: Showstopper
text: Deathrattle: Silence all minions.
flavorText: This act is killing it!

name: Shroud of Concealment
text: Draw 2 minions. Any played this turn gain Stealth for 1 turn.
flavorText: This page left intentionally blank.

name: Sightless Watcher
text: Battlecry: Look at 3 cards in your deck. Choose one to put on top.
flavorText: What he lacks in sight, he makes up for in sleight-of-tentacle tricks.

name: Sigil of Alacrity
text: At the start of your next turn, draw a card and reduce its Cost by (1).
flavorText: Red means stop. Purple means GO REALLY FAST.

name: Sigil of Flame
text: At the start of your next turn, deal 3 damage to all minions.
flavorText: "Huh, it reads F-I-R-E. Wonder what that means?"

name: Sigil of Silence
text: At the start of your next turn, Silence all enemy minions.
flavorText: A little heard-of spell.

name: Sigil of Summoning
text: At the start of your next turn, summon two 2/2 Demons with Taunt.
flavorText: Look, summoning ain’t exactly a science. Sometimes it takes a turn.

name: Silas Darkmoon
text: Battlecry: Choose a direction to rotate all minions.
flavorText: "You might remember me from such attractions as 'Being Shot out of a Cannon' or 'That Carousel Ate My Friend.'"

name: Silverleaf Poison
text: Give your weapon "After your hero attacks, draw a card."
flavorText: Kazakus has taken to a more direct approach in recent times.

name: Sin'dorei Scentfinder
text: Frenzy: Summon four 1/1 Hyenas with Rush.
flavorText: Loves candles. Hates deodorant.

name: Sinister Strike
text: Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: There's something about this strike that just feels off. Sinister, even.

name: Siphon Soul
text: Destroy a minion. Restore 3 Health to your hero.
flavorText: You probably should avoid siphoning your own soul. You might create some kind of weird infinite loop.

name: Skeletal Dragon
text: Taunt At the end of your turn, add a Dragon to your hand.
flavorText: I wish to complain about this dragon what I purchased not half an hour ago from this very boutique.

name: Sketchy Information
text: Draw a Deathrattle card that costs (4) or less. Trigger its Deathrattle.
flavorText: "I trust the Forsaken as far as I can smell them. Which, I guess is actually pretty far."

name: Skull of Gul'dan
text: Draw 3 cards. Outcast: Reduce their Cost by (3).
flavorText: A fellow of evil possessed, of most devious shadow. He hath turned on his kin a thousand times, and now, how abhorred in all imagination he is!

name: Slam
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it survives, draw a card.
flavorText: "Dun da dun, dun da dun": if you've heard an ogre sing this, it's too late.

name: Sleepy Dragon
text: Taunt
flavorText: Local villagers call her "Naps Under the Mountain."

name: Smug Senior
text: Taunt. Deathrattle: Add a 5/7 Ghost with Taunt to your hand.
flavorText: You want to see something funny? Go visit him in five years.

name: Snack Run
text: Discover a spell. Restore Health to your hero equal to its Cost.
flavorText: "I'll have two monster churros, a combo box of Yogg-Saron, and one of those turkey legs that ate the Silver Hand Recruit."

name: Snake Trap
text: Secret: When one of your minions is attacked, summon three 1/1 Snakes.
flavorText: Why did it have to be snakes?

name: Snap Freeze
text: Freeze a minion. If it's already Frozen, destroy it.
flavorText: Lick the ice block. I triple-double-dog-dare-you.

name: Sneaky Delinquent
text: Stealth. Deathrattle: Add a 3/1 Ghost with Stealth to your hand.
flavorText: All right, now open your lid and say "Ahh!"

name: Solar Eclipse
text: Your next spell this turn casts twice.
flavorText: When the Moon is between the Sun and the Azeroth.

name: Soldier's Caravan
text: At the start of your turn, summon two 1/1 Silver Hand Recruits.
flavorText: It’s a clown car… for JUSTICE!

name: Soothsayer's Caravan
text: At the start of your turn, copy a spell from your opponent's deck to your hand.
flavorText: With tusks like those, you might call her a "Toothsayer."

name: Sorcerer's Gambit
text: Questline: Cast a Fire, Frost, and Arcane spell. Reward: Draw a spell.
flavorText: After "the incident," the Stockades really had to reevaluate their anti-mage protocols.

name: Sorcerous Substitute
text: Battlecry: If you have Spell Damage, summon a copy of this.
flavorText: This substitute's substitution is a dangerous institution.

name: Soul Mirror
text: Summon copies of enemy minions. They attack their copies.
flavorText: It’s a doppelgang-war!

name: Soul Rend
text: Deal 5 damage to all minions. Destroy a card in your deck for each killed.
flavorText: About as close to feeling guilt as a warlock's ever going to get.

name: Soul Shear
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck.
flavorText: "Just a little off the sides please."

name: Soul of the Forest
text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Summon a 2/2 Treant."
flavorText: "Reforestation" is suddenly a terrifying word.

name: Soulbound Ashtongue
text: Whenever this minion takes damage, also deal that amount to your hero.
flavorText: He claims to be "soulbound," but I just think he's clingy.

name: Soulciologist Malicia
text: Battlecry: For each Soul Fragment in your deck, summon a 3/3 Soul with Rush. ( )
flavorText: If you value your life, don't call it a "soft science."

name: Soulshard Lapidary
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Soul Fragment in your deck to give your hero +5 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Also known as a soul sequincer.

name: South Coast Chieftain
text: Battlecry: If you control another Murloc, deal 2 damage.
flavorText: It got the conch. You let it speak!

name: Southsea Captain
text: Your other Pirates have +1/+1.
flavorText: When he saves enough plunder, he's going to commission an enormous captain's hat. He has hat envy.

name: Southsea Scoundrel
text: Battlecry: Discover a card in your opponent's deck. They draw theirs as well.
flavorText: "…and here we see the Southsea Scoundrel in their natural habitat: a den of scum and villainy."

name: Sow the Soil
text: Choose One - Give your minions +1 Attack; or Summon a 2/2 Treant.
flavorText: "I'M NOT A TAILOR!"

name: Sparkjoy Cheat
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Secret, cast it and draw a card.
flavorText: "These do NOT spark joy!"

name: Spawnpool Forager
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Tinyfin.
flavorText: Putting food on the table requires persistence, enthusiasm, and the finest murloc Gloves of Foraging.

name: Speaker Gidra
text: Rush, Windfury Spellburst: Gain Attack and Health equal to the spell's Cost.
flavorText: If a teacher lectures in a forest, does she even make a sound?

name: Spectral Sight
text: Draw a card. Outcast: Draw another.
flavorText: "Pick a card, any card! Preferably the left- or right-most card."

name: Spectral Sight
text: Draw a card. Outcast: Draw another.
flavorText: "Pick a card, any card! Preferably the left- or right-most card."

name: Sphere of Sapience
text: At the start of your turn, look at your top card. You can put it on the bottom and lose 1 Durability.
flavorText: This is what it sounds like when spheres scry.

name: Spice Bread Baker
text: Battlecry: Restore Health to your hero equal to your hand size.
flavorText: The secret ingredient is love. And a LOT of butter.

name: Spider Tank
flavorText: "What if we put guns on it?" -Fizzblitz, staring at the spider-transportation-machine

name: Spiked Wheel
text: Has +3 Attack while your hero has Armor.
flavorText: Great for driving, terrible for steering.

name: Spirit Alpha
text: After you play a card with Overload, summon a 2/3 Spirit Wolf with Taunt.
flavorText: Just like in the natural world, the alpha of the species is bright purple.

name: Spirit Healer
text: After you cast a Holy spell, give a random friendly minion +2 Health.
flavorText: "You again? What did I tell you about trying to fight ALL the quilboars."

name: Spirit Jailer
text: Battlecry: Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck.
flavorText: "Sure, they're in your deck, but the mind is like, the REAL prison."

name: Sprint
text: Draw 4 cards.
flavorText: Rogues are not good joggers.

name: Spymistress
text: Stealth
flavorText: Spies in Outland must blend into the environment. That means hot-pink gear and bright green hair. It’s a weird place.

name: Stage Dive
text: Draw a Rush minion. Corrupt: Give it +2/+1.
flavorText: The most metal trust fall.

name: Stage Hand
text: Battlecry: Give a random minion in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: Holds everything himself because people wouldn't stop touching the prop table.

name: Stand Against Darkness
text: Summon five 1/1 Silver Hand Recruits.
flavorText: Or if you're too tired, you can just kind of lean against the darkness.

name: Star Student Stelina
text: Outcast: Look at 3 cards in your opponent's hand. Shuffle one of them into their deck.
flavorText: Cheating is just using your resources wisely.

name: Starscryer
text: Deathrattle: Draw a spell.
flavorText: Often grieves with the Starsweeper.

name: Stealer of Souls
text: After you draw a card, change its Cost to Health instead of Mana.
flavorText: The tooth fairy gig didn't work out.

name: Steeldancer
text: Battlecry: Summon a random minion with Cost equal to your weapon's Attack.
flavorText: Pretty powerful if you blade your cards right.

name: Steward of Scrolls
text: Spell Damage +1 Battlecry: Discover a spell.
flavorText: Oh dang it, I spilled ink elemental all over my essay!

name: Stiltstepper
text: Battlecry: Draw a card. If you play it this turn, give your hero +4 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Circus school was tough, sometimes you had to step on people to make it to the top.

name: Stockades Guard
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion Taunt.
flavorText: "You there! Defend this prison with your life. It's my break."

name: Stockades Prisoner
text: Starts Dormant. After you play 3 cards, this awakens.
flavorText: She was arrested for lockpicking. Her imprisonment was not well thought out.

name: Stonemaul Anchorman
text: Rush Frenzy: Draw a card.
flavorText: "Brug will read anything you put on the parchment prompter. Anything."

name: Stoneskin Basilisk
text: Divine Shield Poisonous
flavorText: He got that way from looking into a mirror.

name: Stormstrike
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: When your phone is at 5%.

name: Stormwatcher
text: Windfury
flavorText: Aspiring meteorologist!

name: Stormwind Champion
text: Your other minions have +1/+1.
flavorText: When Deathwing assaulted the capital, this soldier was the only member of his squad to survive. Now he's all bitter and stuff.

name: Stormwind Freebooter
text: Battlecry: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn.
flavorText: "Just don't stab the ankles! I want his boots!"

name: Stormwind Guard
text: Taunt Battlecry: Give adjacent minions +1/+1.
flavorText: 1% Guarding, 99% providing directions.

name: Stormwind Piper
text: After this minion attacks, give your Beasts +1/+1.
flavorText: Throws crazy parties with the Rat King—except when it's raining.

name: Stranglethorn Tiger
text: Stealth
flavorText: The wonderful thing about tigers is tigers are wonderful things!

name: Strongman
text: Taunt Corrupt: This costs (0).
flavorText: Sure, it looks impressive until you realize it's a barrel of helium.

name: Stubborn Suspect
text: Deathrattle: Summon a random 3-Cost minion.
flavorText: He keeps saying "I'll never talk," but no one has actually asked him anything.

name: Suckerhook
text: At the end of your turn, transform your weapon into one that costs (1) more.
flavorText: A moderately better dining companion than Suckerbeard.

name: Sunreaver Spy
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: She's watching. Always watching.

name: Sunscale Raptor
text: Frenzy: Shuffle a Sunscale Raptor into your deck with permanent +2/+1.
flavorText: And they don't stop coming and they don't stop coming and they don't stop coming and they don't stop coming and they don't stop coming and they don't stop coming and they—

name: Sunwell Initiate
text: Frenzy: Gain Divine Shield.
flavorText: Initiates don’t study pronunciation until level 20.

name: Sunwing Squawker
text: Battlecry: Repeat the last spell you've cast on a friendly minion on this.
flavorText: Most parrots repeat curses, not blessings.

name: Supreme Abyssal
text: Can't attack heroes.
flavorText: Yet, you still feel attacked.

name: Survival of the Fittest
text: Give +4/+4 to all minions in your hand, deck, and battlefield.
flavorText: Sometimes the fittest is the one smart enough to not start a fight with seven 6/6 Treants.

name: Swashburglar
text: Battlecry: Add a random card from another class to your hand.
flavorText: Was almost named "Swashb-AAAARRHHH-gler"

name: Sweet Tooth
text: Corrupt: Gain +2 Attack and Stealth.
flavorText: He's been eyeballing that ice cream cone all day!

name: Swindle
text: Draw a spell. Combo: And a minion.
flavorText: You know, it's probably just cheaper to find a place that sells the plushie…

name: Swinetusk Shank
text: After you play a Poison, gain +1 Durability.
flavorText: Comes with a rack of ribs!

name: Sword Eater
text: Taunt Battlecry: Equip a 3/2 Sword.
flavorText: How tough is he? He eats swords for breakfast! Without any milk.

name: Sword and Board
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. Gain 2 Armor.
flavorText: Stab and Slab. Charge and Targe. Slash and Bash. You get the idea.

name: Sword of the Fallen
text: After your hero attacks, cast a Secret from your deck.
flavorText: Hoarding secrets is no fun, so play each and every one.

name: Taelan Fordring
text: Taunt, Divine Shield Deathrattle: Draw your highest Cost minion.
flavorText: After growing up with the Scarlet Crusade for most of his life, Taelan finally realized they were maybe not the nicest people.

name: Taintheart Tormenter
text: Taunt Your opponent's spells cost (2) more.
flavorText: Oh boo hoo, did someone's World Tree burn down?

name: Talented Arcanist
text: Battlecry: Your next spell this turn has Spell Damage +2.
flavorText: "Ey mon, you don't get this good just on raw talent ... but it helps."

name: Tame Beast (Rank 1)
text: Summon a 2/2 Beast with Rush. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: "Trust me laddie, I never eat seafood!"

name: Tamsin Roame
text: Whenever you cast a Shadow spell that costs (1) or more, add a copy to your hand that costs (0).
flavorText: In life, Tamsin Roame was one of the Alliance's most promising mages; now she is the Horde's most dangerous warlock.

name: Taurajo Brave
text: Frenzy: Destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: "He's brave, but splinters will make any Tauren cry."

name: Tavish Stormpike
text: After a friendly Beast attacks, summon a Beast from your deck that costs (1) less.
flavorText: "Hurry up, laddie, we're getting overrun! Serpents everywhere! They may look cute, but do ye see the fury in their eyes?!" —Tavish Stormpike

name: Teacher's Pet
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon a random 3-Cost Beast.
flavorText: Really goes the extra mile to get the Hay+.

name: Temple Enforcer
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion +3 Health.
flavorText: He also moonlights Thursday nights as a bouncer at the Pig and Whistle Tavern.

name: Tent Trasher
text: Rush. Costs (1) less for each friendly minion with a unique minion type.
flavorText: "I consider it redecorating."

name: Tenwu of the Red Smoke
text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion to your hand. It costs (1) this turn.
flavorText: Red, the color of subtlety.

name: Teron Gorefiend
text: Battlecry: Destroy all other friendly minions. Deathrattle: Resummon them with +1/+1.
flavorText: "You’re fine, friendly minions! You're fine! Don’t tell Mom!"

name: Terrorguard Escapee
text: Battlecry: Summon three 1/1 Huntresses for your opponent.
flavorText: Poor guy is terrified, look at his faces.

name: The Dark Portal
text: Draw a minion. If you have at least 8 cards in hand, it costs (5) less.
flavorText: Some say it's the source of Azeroth's greatest problems—aside from the gnomes.

name: The Demon Seed
text: Questline: Take 8 damage on your turns. Reward: Lifesteal. Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: Just need some elbow grease to get this working. Oh, and your soul.

name: The Lurker Below
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to an enemy minion. If it dies, repeat on one of its neighbors.
flavorText: "Throw it back! THROW IT BACK!"

name: The Nameless One
text: Battlecry: Choose a minion. Become a 4/4 copy of it, then Silence it.
flavorText: Used to be called " , the Nameless," but everyone got confused.

name: The Rat King
text: Rush. Deathrattle: Go Dormant. Revive after 5 friendly minions die.
flavorText: "I'm the giant rat that makes all of da rules!"

name: Thickhide Kodo
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Gain 5 Armor.
flavorText: The introduction of professions was devastating for kodo populations.

name: Thorngrowth Sentries
text: Summon two 1/2 Turtles with Taunt.
flavorText: Maybe we shouldn't drink from this Oasis…

name: Thrive in the Shadows
text: Discover a spell from your deck.
flavorText: Why would your spells be afraid of the dark? It's easier to nap there.

name: Throw Glaive
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it dies, add a temporary copy of this to your hand.
flavorText: "No, no, I said SHOW me the glaive!"

name: Tickatus
text: Battlecry: Remove the top 5 cards from your deck. Corrupt: Your opponent's deck instead.
flavorText: "These are all.... EXPIRED!"

name: Ticket Master
text: Deathrattle: Shuffle 3 Tickets into your deck. When drawn, summon a 3/3 Plush Bear.
flavorText: You can exchange one ticket for a bear or save up thousands for a tacky light-up paperweight!

name: Tidal Surge
text: Lifesteal Deal 4 damage to a minion.
flavorText: Also good for removing pesky stains.

name: Tidal Wave
text: Lifesteal Deal 3 damage to all minions.
flavorText: "Hang Four, mon!"

name: Tiny Knight of Evil
text: Whenever you discard a card, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: "No, no, no. I asked for a tiny JESTER of evil."

name: Tiny Toys
text: Summon four random 5-Cost minions. Make them 2/2.
flavorText: Mom, they're action figures!

name: Tinyfin's Caravan
text: At the start of your turn, draw a Murloc.
flavorText: Movin' right along, mrgl mrg mrgl mrg.

name: Tirion Fordring
text: Divine Shield, Taunt Deathrattle: Equip a 5/3 Ashbringer.
flavorText: If you haven't heard the Tirion Fordring theme song, it's because it doesn't exist.

name: Toad of the Wilds
text: Taunt Battlecry: If you're holding a Nature spell, gain +2 Health.
flavorText: "Someday we'll find it. The Oasis Connection. The peons, the caravans, and me."

name: Tomb Pillager
text: Deathrattle: Add a Coin to your hand.
flavorText: After the guild broke up, he could no longer raid the tombs.

name: Torrent
text: Deal 8 damage to a minion. Costs (3) less if you cast a spell last turn.
flavorText: Weeks of underwater cross-training have really built up her fourarms.

name: Totem Goliath
text: Deathrattle: Summon all four basic Totems. Overload: (1)
flavorText: It was an art project, and nobody knew when to stop.

name: Totemic Reflection
text: Give a minion +2/+2. If it's a Totem, summon a copy of it.
flavorText: "Upon reflection, I have decided that your board needs more ME."

name: Touch of the Nathrezim
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it dies, restore 4 Health to your hero.
flavorText: "You're giving your soul to me? I'm touched."

name: Tour Guide
text: Battlecry: Your next Hero Power costs (0).
flavorText: "Here is the original blueprint for the Academy grounds! Don't mind those so-called dark chambers… They'll be at the end of the tour."

name: Toxicologist
text: Battlecry: Give your weapon +1 Attack.
flavorText: Double-majoring in culinary sciences was definitely a mistake.

name: Tracking
text: Discover a card from your deck.
flavorText: For the person who just cannot decide what card to put into a deck!

name: Trampling Rhino
text: Rush. After this attacks and kills a minion, excess damage hits the enemy hero.
flavorText: "Whew. I thought you said 'Trampoline Rhino.' Now that would have been scary."

name: Transfer Student
text: This has different effects based on which game board you're on.
flavorText: Oh, the places you'll go! There is so much to fight! There are boards to be explored. There are dreams to take flight.

name: Traveling Merchant
text: Tradeable Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each other friendly minion you control.
flavorText: Northrend's greatest export: funnel cakes.

name: Trick Totem
text: At the end of your turn, cast a random spell that costs (3) or less.
flavorText: It knows how to sit still and do tricks. Still working on rolling over, though.

name: Troublemaker
text: At the end of your turn, summon two 3/3 Ruffians that attack random enemies.
flavorText: "Prepare for trouble!" "Make it double!"

name: Trueaim Crescent
text: After your Hero attacks a minion, your minions attack it too.
flavorText: You could have just pointed.

name: Truesilver Champion
text: Whenever your hero attacks, restore 2 Health to it.
flavorText: It Slices, it Dices. You can cut a tin can with it. (But you wouldn't want to.)

name: Turalyon, the Tenured
text: Rush. Whenever this attacks a minion, set the defender's Attack and Health to 3.
flavorText: "Let evil flee before righteousness; let the innocent live in peace. Let the day come when none need fear. For that day, I give my life gladly."

name: Tuskpiercer
text: Deathrattle: Draw a Deathrattle minion.
flavorText: It's the Barrens, everything has tusks! The Quilboar have tusks, the boars have tusks, the tusks have tusks.

name: Twilight Deceptor
text: Battlecry: If any hero took damage this turn, draw a Shadow spell.
flavorText: Nobody asks questions if you're carrying a clipboard.

name: Twilight Runner
text: Stealth Whenever this attacks, draw 2 cards.
flavorText: Every morning you find two dead cards at your doorstep.

name: Twisting Nether
text: Destroy all minions.
flavorText: The Twisting Nether is a formless place of magic and illusion and destroyed minions.

name: Two-Faced Investor
text: At the end of your turn, reduce the Cost of a card in your hand by (1). (50% chance to increase.)
flavorText: Should never have opened that joint account...

name: Umbral Owl
text: Rush Costs (1) less for each spell you've cast this game.
flavorText: It sleeps with one eye open.

name: Unbound Elemental
text: After you play a card with Overload, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: Unlike bound elementals, Unbound ones really enjoy a night on the town.

name: Underlight Angling Rod
text: After your Hero attacks, add a random Murloc to your hand.
flavorText: "I said I wanted the ASHbringer not FISHbringer!"

name: Unstable Felbolt
text: Deal 3 damage to an enemy minion and a random friendly one.
flavorText: Warning! Your minions are seated in the splash zone.

name: Unstable Shadow Blast
text: Deal 6 damage to a minion. Excess damage hits your hero.
flavorText: "Unstable" usually means "awesome!"

name: Vanessa VanCleef
text: Combo: Add a copy of the last card your opponent played to your hand.
flavorText: Some people collect stamps or flowers. She collects enemies.

name: Varden Dawngrasp
text: Battlecry: Freeze all enemy minions. If any are already Frozen, deal 4 damage to them instead.
flavorText: Varden Dawngrasp could wield fire, summon hailstorms, and morph a night elf into a sheep with a snap of their fingers. Knowing how malleable reality could be, certain labels felt downright trivial.

name: Varian, King of Stormwind
text: Battlecry: Draw a Rush minion to gain Rush. Repeat for Taunt and Divine Shield.
flavorText: Man, this guy is so cool. Sure hope nothing happens to him.

name: Vectus
text: Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Whelps. Each gains a Deathrattle from your minions that died this game.
flavorText: Don’t let that dark magic worry you. He’ll ensure they hatch without a scratch.

name: Vengeful Spirit
text: Outcast: Draw 2 Deathrattle minions.
flavorText: Sheesh, even the spirits are edgy when it comes to Demon Hunters.

name: Venomous Scorpid
text: Poisonous Battlecry: Discover a spell.
flavorText: Despite what Guff says, he is NOT a "nice little guy."

name: Venomstrike Bow
text: Poisonous
flavorText: "You know you only have to coat the arrowhead in poison and not the entire bow, right?"

name: Veteran Warmedic
text: After you cast a Holy spell, summon a 2/2 Medic with Lifesteal.
flavorText: In times of war, warmedics bring their own medics.

name: Vibrant Squirrel
text: Deathrattle: Shuffle 4 Acorns into your deck. When drawn, summon a 2/1 Squirrel.
flavorText: Oh, they're cute now. Just wait till they unleash a Savage Roar.

name: Vile Call
text: Summon two 2/2 Demons with Lifesteal.
flavorText: "We're calling to inform you that your vehicle's insurance is about to expire."

name: Vilefiend Trainer
text: Outcast: Summon two 1/1 Demons.
flavorText: My Vilefiend Trainers give me a much better sprint than my Air Gul'dans.

name: Violet Teacher
text: Whenever you cast a spell, summon a 1/1 Violet Apprentice.
flavorText: If you don't pay attention, you may be turned into a pig. And then you get your name on the board.

name: Vivid Spores
text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Resummon this minion."
flavorText: Hey man, I just feel like... death is just a construct of our imaginations, ya know?

name: Void Drinker
text: Taunt. Battlecry: Destroy a Soul Fragment in your deck to gain +3/+3.
flavorText: It has no taste.

name: Void Flayer
text: Battlecry: For each spell in your hand, deal 1 damage to a random enemy minion.
flavorText: The Void, just like onions, has flayers.

name: Void Shard
text: Lifesteal Deal 4 damage.
flavorText: Light's easy. Void's hard.

name: Void Terror
text: Battlecry: Destroy both adjacent minions and gain their Attack and Health.
flavorText: If you put this into your deck, you WILL lose the trust of your other minions.

name: Voidtouched Attendant
text: Both heroes take one extra damage from all sources.
flavorText: Don't TOUCH the Void. You don't know where it's been.

name: Voodoo Doctor
text: Battlecry: Restore 2 Health.
flavorText: Voodoo is an oft-misunderstood art. But it is art.

name: Voracious Reader
text: At the end of your turn, draw until you have 3 cards.
flavorText: But how much of it is skimming?

name: Vulpera Toxinblade
text: Your weapon has +2 Attack.
flavorText: The blade works well enough on its own… but this is just in case.

name: Wailing Vapor
text: After you play an Elemental, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: If you have The Vapors, your Humors might be imbalanced.

name: Wand Thief
text: Combo: Discover a Mage spell.
flavorText: "What’re ya buyin’?”

name: Wandmaker
text: Battlecry: Add a 1-Cost spell from your class to your hand.
flavorText: She creates incredibly affordable wands of all shapes and sizes. But not owls. The owl is all-natural.

name: War Cache
text: Add a random Warrior minion, spell, and weapon to your hand.
flavorText: It's much tidier than Illidan's storage locker.

name: Warglaives of Azzinoth
text: After attacking a minion, your hero may attack again.
flavorText: The blades glow green from things unseen, dark dreams whirling in the felfire gleam.

name: Warglaives of Azzinoth
text: After attacking a minion, your hero may attack again.
flavorText: The blades glow green from things unseen, dark dreams whirling in the felfire gleam.

name: Warhorse Trainer
text: Your Silver Hand Recruits have +1 Attack.
flavorText: He doesn't even get Sundays off. Every day he's hostling.

name: Warmaul Challenger
text: Battlecry: Choose an enemy minion. Battle it to the death!
flavorText: Old gladiator rules: first one to die loses.

name: Warsong Commander
text: After you summon another minion, give it Rush.
flavorText: The Warsong clan is such drama. It's really not worth it to become a commander.

name: Warsong Envoy
text: Frenzy: Gain +1 Attack for each damaged character.
flavorText: "What do you mean we didn’t give the flag to the Druid?"

name: Warsong Outrider
text: Rush
flavorText: When it comes to the Warsong clan, outriders are the insiders.

name: Warsong Wrangler
text: Battlecry: Discover a Beast from your deck. Give all copies of it +2/+1 (wherever they are).
flavorText: "Me? Playing favorites? I love my beasts all the same!"

name: Waste Warden
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to a minion and all others of the same minion type.
flavorText: Recycle that can, or you get the cuffs!

name: Water Elemental
text: Freeze any character damaged by this minion.
flavorText: Don't summon a water elemental at a party. It'll dampen the mood.

name: Water Moccasin
text: Stealth Has Poisonous while you have no other minions.
flavorText: You need to be specific when you're ordering waterproof shoewear.

name: Wave of Apathy
text: Set the Attack of all enemy minions to 1 until your next turn.
flavorText: "Flavor text? Eh. Can’t be bothered."

name: Wealth Redistributor
text: Taunt. Battlecry: Swap the Attack of the highest and lowest Attack minion.
flavorText: WOULD YE LIKE CASH BACK? [ ] YAR HAR [ ] YO HO

name: Webspinner
text: Deathrattle: Add a random Beast card to your hand.
flavorText: Spider cocoons are like little piñatas!

name: Whack-A-Gnoll Hammer
text: After your hero attacks, give a random friendly minion +1/+1.
flavorText: Hogger's most hated attraction.

name: Whetstone Hatchet
text: After your hero attacks, give a minion in your hand +1 Attack.
flavorText: A bad hatchet can make a good spear better.

name: Whirling Combatant
text: Battlecry and Frenzy: Deal 1 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: It's called capoeira! And yes, it is dangerous!

name: Whirlwind
text: Deal 1 damage to ALL minions.
flavorText: The way to tell seasoned warriors from novice ones: the novices yell "wheeeee" while whirlwinding.

name: Wicked Shipment
text: Tradeable Summon 1/1 (Imp, Imps). (Upgrades by 2 when Traded!)
flavorText: All horns on deck!

name: Wicked Stab (Rank 1)
text: Deal 2 damage. (Upgrades when you have 5 Mana.)
flavorText: Always go for the glowing weak point.

name: Wicked Whispers
text: Discard your lowest Cost card. Give your minions +1/+1.
flavorText: When the Old Ones whisper, others will scream.

name: Wickerclaw
text: After your hero gains Attack, this minion gains +2 Attack.
flavorText: They say pets tend to look like their owners.

name: Wild Growth
text: Gain an empty Mana Crystal.
flavorText: Grow your own mana crystals with this Mana Crystal Growth Kit, only 39.99!

name: Wildfire
text: Increase the damage of your Hero Power by 1.
flavorText: The Barrens were a lush jungle. Then this happened.

name: Windfury
text: Give a minion Windfury.
flavorText: Windfury is like Earthfury and Firefury, but more light and airy.

name: Wolpertinger
text: Battlecry: Summon a copy of this.
flavorText: Scholomance student Brewfest prank gone awry.

name: Worgen Infiltrator
text: Stealth
flavorText: If you want to stop a worgen from infiltrating, just yell, "No! Bad boy!"

name: Wound Prey
text: Deal 1 damage. Summon a 1/1 Hyena with Rush.
flavorText: You steal the cranberry juice, you pay the price.

name: Wretched Tutor
text: Spellburst: Deal 2 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: "If you like my tutoring, you'll love my sister the art therapist, my father the driver, and my mother the housekeeper."

name: Wriggling Horror
text: Battlecry: Give adjacent minions +1/+1.
flavorText: Created to scare. Born to wriggle.

name: Wyrm Weaver
text: Spellburst: Summon two 1/2 Mana Wyrms.
flavorText: Studied basket weaving as an undergrad.

name: Xyrella
text: Battlecry: If you've restored Health this turn, deal that much damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: On the Night of Falling Stars, Xyrella had a vision of a shattered naaru. "Go to the Barrens," the being said. "Seek the shards of my broken body. Restore me, and I will restore your daughter."

name: Y'Shaarj, the Defiler
text: Battlecry: Add a copy of each Corrupted card you've played this game to your hand. They cost (0) this turn.
flavorText: Y'Shaarj made an excellent office intern, doing the copying AND defiling.

name: Yogg-Saron, Master of Fate
text: Battlecry: If you've cast 10 spells this game, spin the Wheel of Yogg-Saron. ( left!) (Ready!)
flavorText: Yogg take the wheel!

name: Yoink!
text: Discover a Hero Power and set its Cost to (0). Swap back after 2 uses.
flavorText: Saying the spell’s name makes it work better.

name: Young Priestess
text: At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Health.
flavorText: She can't wait to learn Power Word: Fortitude Rank 2.

name: Youthful Brewmaster
text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion from the battlefield to your hand.
flavorText: His youthful enthusiasm doesn’t always equal excellence in his brews. Don’t drink the Mogu Stout!

name: Ysera the Dreamer
text: Battlecry: Add one of each Dream card to your hand.
flavorText: Quick! Quick! Write it down before you forget them all!

name: Ysiel Windsinger
text: Your spells cost (1).
flavorText: Reach down into your lungs. The wind that resides there is your greatest treasure. It provides the gift of song, which is free. *But not less than (1)

name: Zai, the Incredible
text: Battlecry: Copy the left- and right-most cards in your hand.
flavorText: Following this act will be her younger brother, Frank the Mediocre.

name: Zixor, Apex Predator
text: Rush Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Zixor Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: A living terror. Teleports at will. Feasts on tainted helboar meat. No head scritches unless you're Leoroxx.
